Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.07,0:00:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Money trumps peace, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.71,0:00:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in our world, let's take the UN.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.99,0:00:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The UN calibrates about 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.87,0:00:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In the UN, routinely, money always trumps peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.17,0:00:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They've never had peace once.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.74,0:00:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Money always trumps peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.70,0:00:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All the UN is all the 198 countries
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.98,0:00:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,dealing with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.12,0:00:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you these oil contracts,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.84,0:01:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you give me this, we'll lower the import tariff on cotton
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.48,0:01:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and you compensate with a little gasoline money.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.14,0:01:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's deal-making, deal-making, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.92,0:01:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only self-interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.46,0:01:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The League of Nations didn't work either
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.46,0:01:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,for the same reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.30,0:01:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,because people are way too self-centered.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.94,0:01:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd have to be quite high to give up a gain
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.64,0:01:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for the good of the world, for the good of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.83,0:01:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you ask them about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.99,0:01:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,say, look, I'm a politician, I'm not a saint.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.38,0:01:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Business is business.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.16,0:01:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Halliburton made $90 billion so far in this war
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.56,0:01:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and moved to Dubai, where the taxes are lower.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.03,0:01:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't want to even help pay for the war
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.99,0:01:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that they're making the $90 billion off of.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.38,0:01:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the biggest, one of the multi-billionaires
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.98,0:01:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that finances the far left, interestingly,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.82,0:02:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,bought $400 million worth of Halliburton stock.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.15,0:02:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I think, you see what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.85,0:02:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a big protagonist of all far left causes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.39,0:02:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And when Halliburton moved to Dubai
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.19,0:02:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and they wouldn't have to pay the taxes,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.55,0:02:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,he saw the, you know, the $400 million
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.33,0:02:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,or $400 billion or something, he's so rich
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.03,0:02:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that billions and trillions of them .
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.44,0:02:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, U.S. philanthropists, you see, are 455.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.11,0:02:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The United Nations is not a philanthropic organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.21,0:02:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,None of them give any money to the United Nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.13,0:02:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,None of them give any money to anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.28,0:02:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They calibrate it 180 to 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.37,0:02:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So here you're vilifying America,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.89,0:02:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the most humanitarian country in world history.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.18,0:02:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the richest of the rich calibrated 455, uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.42,0:03:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you condemn America and say, well, we should turn,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.60,0:03:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll never forget that politician in the last election,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.98,0:03:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we should turn to the United Nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.94,0:03:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd turn to the United Nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.08,0:03:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd turn to the United Nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.60,0:03:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So the UN is the sheep's clothing, the sheep's clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.50,0:03:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you see how simple it is, sheep's clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.77,0:03:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the world loves blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.53,0:03:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I just quoted you a couple of,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.93,0:03:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,These philosophers, the one who just died in March,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.21,0:03:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,did America deserve 9-11, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.55,0:04:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's hegemonous and successful, successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.50,0:04:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Blame, blame calibrates at 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.84,0:04:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Look how people hang on to blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.52,0:04:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because blame, the real struggle in our world,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.02,0:04:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is for moral superiority.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.90,0:04:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only two things that count in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.48,0:04:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't kid yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.13,0:04:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The moral high ground and money.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.35,0:04:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the meantime, linking up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.60,0:04:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A 17-year-old sailor's dream come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.16,0:04:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Link up, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.10,0:04:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We never would have gotten to war for it, I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.33,0:04:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In contrast to blame and hate
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.67,0:04:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and all these things that the world clings to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.27,0:04:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and milks them for all they can get out of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.88,0:04:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the Amish response to the murder of the children
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.68,0:04:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.82,0:04:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,540.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.90,0:04:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was the best demonstration of Christianity
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.33,0:05:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and the teachings of Jesus Christ that I've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.57,0:05:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never seen that level of presentation
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.68,0:05:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of the teachings of Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.30,0:05:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive them, for they know now what they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.16,0:05:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.82,0:05:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember what the Amish did.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.12,0:05:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they provided money for the families of the perpetrators
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.10,0:05:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because they knew if they were indicted and put in prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.32,0:05:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the families would be without.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.70,0:05:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They collected food and clothing and all
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.14,0:05:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,for the families of the killers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.72,0:05:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Amish, you know, shamed us all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.30,0:05:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,They really did a magnificent job
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.33,0:05:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of being that which they...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.04,0:05:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,To talk about things is one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.82,0:05:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,To become them is another.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.54,0:05:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Amish really showed us what it means to become
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.36,0:05:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you teach.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.46,0:05:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They became.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.66,0:05:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.20,0:05:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,At 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.06,0:06:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And 540 is unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.62,0:06:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is a whole level.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.98,0:06:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,0.4% of the world's population ever gets to 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.16,0:06:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess they must all be Amish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.62,0:06:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of them must be Amish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.14,0:06:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest are in AA, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.48,0:06:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I've only told you that AA story.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.42,0:06:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy comes to the meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.56,0:06:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He's all looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.82,0:06:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He's all wimpy and horrible and crying and everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.38,0:06:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, what's the matter with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.24,0:06:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, well, my wife ran up with somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.80,0:06:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and my car got wrecked and the house burned down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.02,0:06:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And they said, yeah, but that was yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.15,0:06:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That was yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.37,0:06:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.88,0:06:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we see from the view point of reality and truth
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.72,0:06:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that phenomena within the world
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.18,0:06:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,appear as a consequence of the reality of that which they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.26,0:06:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Not by...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.26,0:07:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That which they are labeled.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.82,0:07:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's by virtue of their essence, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.47,0:07:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the whole argument about nominalization falls down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.23,0:07:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Emergence is a principle beyond causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.43,0:07:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And it means because it's the work of the...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.39,0:07:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the work of the whole, both the content and the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.16,0:07:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you throw in evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.30,0:07:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and things begin to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.99,0:07:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We say, what you're seeing is potentiality becoming actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.89,0:07:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,because of local conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.42,0:07:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the local conditions is intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.55,0:07:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention for a thing to come about increases the likelihood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.38,0:07:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't control it, but it adds a powerful thing to the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.52,0:07:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So emergence, you see, phenomena are not occurring as a result of causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.27,0:08:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Causality is based on mechanism.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.43,0:08:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's based on logistic materialism and the laws of Newtonian logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.10,0:08:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Phenomena become their own potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.67,0:08:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you're seeing is not really evolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.80,0:08:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're seeing the emergence of this transforming into that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.80,0:08:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You're really seeing transformation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.05,0:08:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness calibration itself is 6.05.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.75,0:08:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's five points higher than the 600 level.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.67,0:08:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Five points higher because it does add some additional information
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.74,0:08:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to what is learned.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.74,0:08:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Opinion is 140.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.09,0:08:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, opinion is all narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.09,0:08:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So my tube, my face, me, me, me websites
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.38,0:08:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,are then the glorification of narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.38,0:09:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So consciousness calibration, one reason it's 6.05,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.50,0:09:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is it eliminates your personal perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.50,0:09:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Personal opinion about the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.50,0:09:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do it correctly, it eliminates it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.50,0:09:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter what you think about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.82,0:09:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at it, your pupil will instantly calibrate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.36,0:09:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beyond personal opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.90,0:09:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.19,0:09:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Calling a spade a spade is not popular in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.99,0:09:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,There were some things I was going to present this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.99,0:09:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We asked the arm and said no.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.99,0:09:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.21,0:09:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't always call a spade a spade
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.21,0:09:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,about everything, anytime, anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.26,0:09:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So discretion, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.26,0:09:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Discretion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.18,0:09:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Discretion means that you just can't blab everything
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.18,0:09:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,without taking any responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.18,0:10:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,for the context in which you're saying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.54,0:10:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an old Christian.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.54,0:10:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I never liked the term,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.54,0:10:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,don't throw your pearls before a swine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.54,0:10:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds insulting, you know, a swine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.54,0:10:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But I know what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.54,0:10:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.54,0:10:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, what it means is you can't just blab everything
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.54,0:10:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and anything without responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.54,0:10:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,for the same reason you can't shout fire in a theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.54,0:10:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't just shout fire in a theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.54,0:10:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But what we're seeing now is fire being shouted
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.54,0:10:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,in the theater of the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.54,0:10:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Calling a spade a spade, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.80,0:10:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is different than the apologist.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.80,0:10:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The apologist is at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.80,0:10:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The apologist tries to pretend,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.80,0:10:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, they're just harmless good folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.80,0:10:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When I say good folks,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.78,0:10:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,why is your vest bulging?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.78,0:11:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, little bombs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.80,0:11:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.83,0:11:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, little bombs to blow up the busload of the children, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.83,0:11:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.83,0:11:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Calling a spade a spade, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.02,0:11:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is part of spiritual integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.02,0:11:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to standing up for the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.02,0:11:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to make a public display about that,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.02,0:11:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but you yourself should be willing to do that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.02,0:11:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of being an apologist for truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.02,0:11:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,for untruth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.02,0:11:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,To become an apologist, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.02,0:11:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens when you're an apologist for evil
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.02,0:11:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is you become aligned with that energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.98,0:11:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You pick up the karma of being the supporter of non-integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.07,0:11:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If you cheer on and make excuses
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.58,0:11:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for that which is vicious and cruel,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.65,0:11:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.65,0:11:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,then you pay the price.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.65,0:11:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The karmic consequence of the apologist
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.77,0:12:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you share in the consequences
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.77,0:12:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which you are apologizing for.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.77,0:12:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's ask if that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.77,0:12:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.69,0:12:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you're an apologist for that which is non-integrous,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.69,0:12:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,make excuses for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.04,0:12:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you now share in that karmic responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.04,0:12:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and the karmic consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.04,0:12:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So we said that is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.04,0:12:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,one explanation for many of the phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.04,0:12:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we see in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.17,0:12:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Major tragedies, whole groups,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.20,0:12:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,whole cultures are beset.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.20,0:12:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you go back and do research,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.58,0:12:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find karmically,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.58,0:12:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,they're the same people
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.58,0:12:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that were the invaders
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.00,0:12:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that slaughtered all the innocents,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.00,0:12:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the Vikings, the Huns, the Visigoths.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.00,0:12:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got the history of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.00,0:12:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The Huns, the Visigoths,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.02,0:12:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,one after another,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.02,0:12:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the barbarians swept through
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.21,0:13:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and killed everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.01,0:13:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Mongolian emperors.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.01,0:13:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They killed whole masses of people,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.01,0:13:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,whole countries, whole cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.01,0:13:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They killed whole cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.71,0:13:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see there's a collective karmic debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.71,0:13:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Collective karmic debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.71,0:13:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.78,0:13:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see the evolutionary stages of mankind in society.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.97,0:13:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Much is made out of slavery, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.97,0:13:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,People are still trying to milk it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.97,0:13:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,like George Washington did.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.10,0:13:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Slavery was a condition of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.10,0:13:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,all of mankind, until recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.10,0:13:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it still goes on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.22,0:13:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The last country only made it illegal in 1988.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.22,0:13:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was a financial benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.18,0:13:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's chase back slavery
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.18,0:13:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and see if we can find out what's the truth about it
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.18,0:13:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of all the political BS.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.04,0:14:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In the days of the barbarians,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.39,0:14:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the Goths, the Visigoths,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.39,0:14:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,all the giant hordes,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.22,0:14:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the Vikings especially,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.22,0:14:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,they swarmed over Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.61,0:14:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and various cultures, again,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.61,0:14:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and did the same thing in the Orient.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.61,0:14:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And they killed everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.06,0:14:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They chopped them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.63,0:14:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,When they got through with an invasion,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.63,0:14:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the skulls, the chopped off skulls
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.63,0:14:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,were heaped 100 feet in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.63,0:14:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Thousands of skulls
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.63,0:14:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of the people chopped off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.63,0:14:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.63,0:14:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He was supposed to chop your head off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.21,0:14:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Some bright Viking somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.83,0:14:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of killing him,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.31,0:14:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we could sell him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.31,0:14:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so instead of killing the conquered,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.82,0:14:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the later kings of Africa,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.82,0:14:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,who were the basis of the slave trade
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.82,0:14:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're familiar with,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.82,0:14:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,discovered instead of killing all the members
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.86,0:14:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of the opposite tribe,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.86,0:15:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you could sell them for good money.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.86,0:15:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.61,0:15:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Slavery was the nature of man.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.61,0:15:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ancient Greece, most people,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.61,0:15:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,were slaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.61,0:15:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Nine out of ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.61,0:15:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Ancient Rome, nine out of ten slaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.90,0:15:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Slavery was a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.90,0:15:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And forget it was a caste society.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.90,0:15:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Caste society.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.02,0:15:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The emperor at the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.02,0:15:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The slaves are at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.02,0:15:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, who else is going to do the labor
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.02,0:15:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,except slaves?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.02,0:15:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you get slaves? You buy them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.02,0:15:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So they became like cattle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.44,0:15:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.49,0:15:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now don't you see the benefit of slavery
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.49,0:15:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is if you got your choice
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.49,0:15:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,between having your head severed
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.87,0:15:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,or picking cotton,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.87,0:15:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,which would you take?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.54,0:15:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I got family and kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.54,0:15:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to put up with whatever goes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.54,0:15:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,with being alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.67,0:15:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that in Prisoners of War.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.67,0:15:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They will put up with whatever it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.67,0:16:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.06,0:16:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So slavery then was a step above,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.06,0:16:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,a step forward for mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.06,0:16:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You let people live then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.54,0:16:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget they were as valuable
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.54,0:16:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,as livestock.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.54,0:16:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So you took care of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.63,0:16:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So the lifetime, the length of life
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.63,0:16:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of a slave in early America
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.63,0:16:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,was 15 years longer
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.11,0:16:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,than if he had stayed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.11,0:16:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in his native Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.78,0:16:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He lived 15 years longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.78,0:16:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He had protection. He had vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.78,0:16:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He had dentistry. He had doctors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.14,0:16:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He had shelter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.14,0:16:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't killed by neighboring tribes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.14,0:16:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So his life was survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.14,0:16:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So he became valuable.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.14,0:16:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,At least as valuable as cattle, horses,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.14,0:16:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,sheep, dogs, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.45,0:16:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a step up for mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.45,0:16:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course the reason the South
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.45,0:16:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,hung onto the slaves is because
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.45,0:16:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,they had all their money invested in slaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.45,0:16:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't just a goody-goody moral deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.48,0:16:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you had all your money invested
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.48,0:17:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in slaves and somebody wants
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.48,0:17:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to make them illegal,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.48,0:17:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you're about to go bankrupt.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.48,0:17:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So the whole economy of the South
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.48,0:17:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,was based on the economy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.48,0:17:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the moral, ethical situation
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.48,0:17:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of the slaves,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.48,0:17:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but economic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.51,0:17:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see when you recontextualize
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.51,0:17:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,a thing and put it in
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.51,0:17:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,historical background,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.51,0:17:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it looks different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.66,0:17:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The ancestors of every
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.66,0:17:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,person in this room
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.66,0:17:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,were slaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.18,0:17:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I just said it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.18,0:17:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Every person in this room,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.06,0:17:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,your ancestors were slaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.06,0:17:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just how many centuries
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.06,0:17:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,do you want to go back?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.31,0:17:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm of English, Scottish, Irish descent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.95,0:17:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm sure it was the Vikings
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.95,0:17:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that slaughtered my forbearers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.95,0:17:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can track it out
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.11,0:18:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,with genetic tracing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.11,0:18:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So in other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.66,0:18:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to do a make wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.66,0:18:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,if you take a thing out
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.58,0:18:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of the context of history,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.58,0:18:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you can make a make wrong out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.58,0:18:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course today's world
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.58,0:18:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly tries to juice everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.58,0:18:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Tries to juice race,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.58,0:18:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,sex, gender, the whole business,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.58,0:18:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,age, tries to juice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.65,0:18:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would they want to juice it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.65,0:18:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the ego gets its juice
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.65,0:18:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,out of conflict,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.65,0:18:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,tension.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.03,0:18:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd say that's the problem
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.03,0:18:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in spiritual evolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.03,0:18:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is you have to give up the juice
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.03,0:18:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're getting out of a position.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.03,0:18:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this one,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.10,0:18:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to the narcissistic core of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.10,0:18:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is almost irresistible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.10,0:18:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is to be superior
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.10,0:18:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and to be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.10,0:18:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So the whole core of narcissism,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.51,0:18:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,relativism,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.61,0:18:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is the narcissistic core of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.61,0:18:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You would rather lie
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.41,0:19:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and be right
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.79,0:19:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,than be truthful
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.79,0:19:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and not have a cause
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.79,0:19:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can beat a drum about
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.79,0:19:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and get a parade going.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.14,0:19:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, calling a spade a spade
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.14,0:19:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,then is honesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.49,0:19:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And the wolf in sheep's clothing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.87,0:19:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated, I was surprised
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.87,0:19:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,how low it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.87,0:19:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It was really lower than many other things
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.87,0:19:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that you would think would be worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.94,0:19:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something more severe
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.94,0:19:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritually
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.94,0:19:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,about deception.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.38,0:19:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as the rape
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.63,0:19:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and seduction of children
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.63,0:19:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is a worse crime
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.66,0:19:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,than the seduction of adults.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.66,0:19:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The seduction of the innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.66,0:19:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the wolf in sheep's clothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.66,0:19:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Little Red Riding Hood,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.66,0:19:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,how does the story go?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.66,0:19:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Little Red Riding Hood.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.30,0:19:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,How does the story go?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.30,0:19:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Little Red Riding Hood.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.22,0:19:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,She's gone, she's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.80,0:20:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you remembered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.80,0:20:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The wolf in sheep's clothing, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.22,0:20:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, social equality
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.22,0:20:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States is guaranteed
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.22,0:20:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,by the United States Constitution
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.22,0:20:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,at $5.50.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.22,0:20:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, sexism and racism
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.22,0:20:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and all those things are at $1.80.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.22,0:20:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So to try to do a flip over,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.22,0:20:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,make wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.22,0:20:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you say social equality is guaranteed
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.22,0:20:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,by the United States Constitution
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.22,0:20:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,$5.50.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.54,0:20:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, if it is not provided,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.54,0:20:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we should question how come it's not provided
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.54,0:20:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and do something about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.54,0:20:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So it doesn't mean becoming passive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.02,0:20:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Transparency is $4.25.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.02,0:20:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Deception is $1.60.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.18,0:20:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,$1.60.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.27,0:20:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.27,0:20:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And I,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.14,0:20:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,part of the integrity of spiritual teachers
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.14,0:20:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that I teach is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.14,0:20:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,transparency.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.14,0:20:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The teacher, what the teacher's motives,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.14,0:21:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,goals, everything should be
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.14,0:21:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,transparent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.22,0:21:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Transparent to all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.29,0:21:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I just got an interesting paper
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.29,0:21:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,about a local group
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.29,0:21:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in this week's
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.32,0:21:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,what is it called?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.32,0:21:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Red Rock News.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.32,0:21:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A group that operates in the exact
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.32,0:21:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,opposite of what we've recommended.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.32,0:21:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Exact opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.32,0:21:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Transparency means
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.32,0:21:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is open, you've got nothing to hide
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.32,0:21:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're not resorting
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.32,0:21:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to deception.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.32,0:21:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth itself
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.54,0:21:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates as a concept
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.54,0:21:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,at $4.75.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.54,0:21:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Latin version
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.54,0:21:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,$4.85, somewhat high because
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.54,0:21:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,it comes out of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.54,0:21:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,greater history.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.54,0:21:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Slander and false
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.54,0:21:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,witness is as low as
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.54,0:21:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,$75.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.02,0:21:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it must be very difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.02,0:21:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a politician.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.24,0:22:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.00,0:22:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Other than the U.S.,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.00,0:22:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,politicians lie over 99%
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.00,0:22:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of the time, 100% of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.00,0:22:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Outside the U.S.,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.64,0:22:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,politicians lie about 100% of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.64,0:22:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,99%.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.09,0:22:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In the U.S.,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.09,0:22:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if it's over 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.09,0:22:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In the U.S., it's
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.28,0:22:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,truthful over 90%.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.35,0:22:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.35,0:22:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Politicians, as a matter
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.25,0:22:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.31,0:22:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,are forced to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.66,0:22:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,tailor the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.66,0:22:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,close to 100% of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.24,0:22:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of their job.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.24,0:22:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They have to tailor the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.37,0:22:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Tailor the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.37,0:22:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But they're not the quickest
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.37,0:22:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to heaven, right, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.37,0:22:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't substitute a politician
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.37,0:23:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,for the Pope, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.72,0:23:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, social equality.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.72,0:23:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Transparency, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.72,0:23:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth and veritas against slander.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.72,0:23:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.98,0:23:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,here sitting here?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.77,0:23:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The label came up with something.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.72,0:23:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's time to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.72,0:23:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the Bill of Rights,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.34,0:23:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Constitution, and U.S. jurisprudence
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.34,0:23:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,all are extremely high.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.34,0:23:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.34,0:23:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll quit here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.34,0:23:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll resume afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.34,0:23:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Any questions before we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.34,0:23:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody got anything quick and easy?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.50,0:23:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick and easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.59,0:23:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No quick and easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.88,0:23:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, we can reconvene at what time?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.88,0:24:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,At 2 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.81,0:24:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,2 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.06,0:24:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We shall resume.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.34,0:24:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, what slide were we on last week?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.34,0:24:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,103.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.53,0:24:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So how many, let's see,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.53,0:24:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,those new slides, how many did I give you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.53,0:24:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave you four, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.76,0:24:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Four slides on that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.76,0:24:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We're on 103.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.76,0:24:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's 104, 105, and 106.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.76,0:24:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're on 103.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.76,0:24:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We're on 104.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.14,0:24:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So how many more have we got to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.14,0:24:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Two more to go after 104.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.14,0:24:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.14,0:24:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy, I better hustle up.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.82,0:25:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where our sheets were
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.82,0:25:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,when we were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.82,0:25:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, yeah, but those are removed.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.82,0:25:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we got a secret this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.82,0:25:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We learned
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.94,0:25:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,a secret that money
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.94,0:25:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,trumps peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.00,0:25:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That means we can have peace
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.00,0:25:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and you do it via money.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.61,0:25:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We thought you could only get it by war
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.61,0:25:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and killing people.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.70,0:25:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You make sufficient financial adjustments
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.70,0:25:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,around the table
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.70,0:25:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that people would rather have peace
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.70,0:25:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and be rich than war,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.70,0:25:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,which is expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.47,0:25:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So we buy them off.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.60,0:25:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that easy?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.60,0:25:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Give a few shares of Walmart
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.60,0:25:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.60,0:25:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,well, I think there's a certain truth to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.18,0:25:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That money
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.41,0:25:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,money is really the most
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.76,0:25:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,practical way.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.76,0:25:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Money adjustments, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.76,0:26:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The way of the secret
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.81,0:26:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to the way of peace is money.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.01,0:26:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You heard it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.26,0:26:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You buy your way to peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.58,0:26:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,People do it, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.58,0:26:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ransom, all those kinds of ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.76,0:26:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because peace
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.76,0:26:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes an ism, peace-ism.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.76,0:26:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes an ideological
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.76,0:26:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,ideological
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.79,0:26:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,politicized thing
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.79,0:26:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,which immediately sets up resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.79,0:26:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately sets up resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.79,0:26:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I thought that was an interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.82,0:26:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.82,0:26:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,thing to notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.82,0:26:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.02,0:26:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even remember where we were.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.02,0:26:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we did the Amish.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.17,0:26:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.78,0:27:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Constitution. Bill of Rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.78,0:27:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein calibrates at 499
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.09,0:27:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's still people writing books
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.09,0:27:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,criticizing Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.09,0:27:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They calibrate at 99.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.09,0:27:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And if Einstein was wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.25,0:27:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,how do they explain
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.25,0:27:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiroshima and Nagasaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.25,0:27:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be an uncomfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.25,0:27:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.46,0:27:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,New Testament minus Revelations
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.46,0:27:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is 880.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.46,0:27:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Secularism is 165.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.46,0:27:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.53,0:27:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,give people a choice,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.53,0:27:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the choice they're making?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.53,0:27:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,To refute
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.72,0:27:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, Christianity
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.72,0:27:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,or spiritual truth
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.72,0:27:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,for secularism
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.72,0:27:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see now why the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.72,0:27:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,calibration level of western world
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.72,0:27:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is sinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.72,0:27:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Because as it
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.72,0:27:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.72,0:27:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,religion is really destroyed
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.72,0:27:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,or under attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.75,0:27:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too busy scuttling its own ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.75,0:28:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at the history of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.00,0:28:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the Episcopal Church in recent decades
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.00,0:28:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, they've scuttled their
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.10,0:28:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,own ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.10,0:28:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The Archbishop of Canterbury who calibrates at 400
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.10,0:28:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,writes a book in which
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.10,0:28:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,he puts in BCE instead of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.10,0:28:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in AC or
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.10,0:28:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,these secularized things.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.10,0:28:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't want to offend
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.13,0:28:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the Muslims.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.90,0:28:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want the Muslims reading the New Testament.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.99,0:28:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.99,0:28:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They've got their own book.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.99,0:28:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.36,0:28:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, it's scuttling its own
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.36,0:28:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,ship via relativism.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.36,0:28:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Via relativism.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.36,0:28:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Humane Society
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.22,0:28:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 410
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.22,0:28:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and PETA
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.22,0:28:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.22,0:28:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a book called
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.60,0:28:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.59,0:28:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget the name of the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.59,0:28:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it gives you the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.59,0:28:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,background on the people who
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.59,0:29:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,founded like ACLU
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.59,0:29:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,PETA
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.59,0:29:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.66,0:29:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Intellectual Morons I think is the name of the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.66,0:29:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When you read about
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.32,0:29:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the people who founded these organizations
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.32,0:29:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you say, I don't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.32,0:29:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It means all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.32,0:29:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,should be sacrificed
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.32,0:29:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,for the animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.42,0:29:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, it counts between your life
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.42,0:29:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,or an animal's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.42,0:29:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The animal's life should take precedence.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.54,0:29:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.54,0:29:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,relativism is like a complete reversal.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.54,0:29:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,American Civil Rights Union
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.31,0:29:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,ACLU
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.31,0:29:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,versus the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.37,0:29:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,American Civil Liberties Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.66,0:29:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the guy who set up
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.66,0:29:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the Scopes Trial
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.68,0:29:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is the same guy
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.68,0:29:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that founded the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.78,0:29:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,ACLU.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.78,0:29:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,ACLU calibrates at 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.78,0:29:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Its opposite is
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.61,0:29:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the American Civil Rights Union
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.61,0:30:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrates at 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.61,0:30:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This was founded by a bunch of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.61,0:30:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,ministers, I think Protestant ministers
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.61,0:30:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,at 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.86,0:30:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It emphasizes that the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.86,0:30:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Constitution guarantees
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.86,0:30:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the right to freedom of religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.86,0:30:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom of religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.86,0:30:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is why the Pilgrim Fathers came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.86,0:30:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Pilgrim Fathers.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.11,0:30:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We did
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.23,0:30:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't we do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.23,0:30:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, that was number two.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.26,0:30:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.39,0:30:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So now we want number three, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.15,0:30:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we did
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.15,0:30:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,one and two.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.15,0:30:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,After that comes three.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.15,0:30:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,After two comes three, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.35,0:30:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It did until I went to college.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.83,0:30:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Two plus two is four
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.83,0:30:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is a white man oppressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.34,0:30:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so we see
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.34,0:30:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the greatest books written, interestingly,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.34,0:30:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is Extraordinary Popular Delusions
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.34,0:31:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Madness of Crowds
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.34,0:31:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,by Mackey.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.40,0:31:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I think written in the late 1800s,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.40,0:31:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,1980.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.82,0:31:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Extraordinary Popular Delusions and the Madness
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.82,0:31:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of Crowds, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.07,0:31:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.07,0:31:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth's temperature
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.07,0:31:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is of human origin
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.07,0:31:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,as proposed in
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.14,0:31:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Inconvenient Truth. Calibrates at
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.14,0:31:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,180.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.97,0:31:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What humans do is create pollution.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.97,0:31:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But pollution is not
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.97,0:31:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the cause of the Earth warming.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.97,0:31:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And we got a negative on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.97,0:31:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember I was surprised too.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.97,0:31:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.51,0:31:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I investigated further.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.51,0:31:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you don't get an answer that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.51,0:31:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,conforms to what you would imagine,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.51,0:31:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you start doing research.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.51,0:31:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And I found that the Earth's temperature
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.51,0:31:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is due to the magnetic
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.51,0:31:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,activity on the surface of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.51,0:31:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think I've given references
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.06,0:31:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to that before. Science Magazine,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.06,0:32:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Environmental Report
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.12,0:32:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and News.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.12,0:32:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you know, core drillings
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.12,0:32:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Arctic going back
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.12,0:32:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,15,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.12,0:32:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Cyclic temperature
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.12,0:32:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Earth is correlated
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.12,0:32:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,with the sun. When you look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.12,0:32:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,amount of energy the sun puts out
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.12,0:32:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and the size of the sun compared
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.12,0:32:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Earth, you realize that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.12,0:32:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,man's contribution
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.12,0:32:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,through pollution
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.18,0:32:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is 0.8
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.18,0:32:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,degrees Fahrenheit.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.18,0:32:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If we all stopped all polluting,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.18,0:32:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the Earth would cool
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.22,0:32:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,down 0.81
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.22,0:32:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,degrees Fahrenheit.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.22,0:32:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's the cause
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.98,0:32:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,then of pollution?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.98,0:32:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's overpopulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.98,0:32:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it not? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.24,0:32:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So you want to get rid of pollution,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.24,0:32:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to get rid of Earth warming,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.24,0:32:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,pollution is not the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.24,0:32:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you do want to get rid of pollution,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.24,0:32:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you just can't have so many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.24,0:32:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Too many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.24,0:32:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to tell the quick connectors that,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.24,0:33:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.43,0:33:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess quick connectors don't make people.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.43,0:33:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I imagine that's old fashioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.53,0:33:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they call them?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.53,0:33:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Connectors?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.53,0:33:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the website?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.39,0:33:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick connector? What do they call it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.39,0:33:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe I will get reborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.28,0:33:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.48,0:33:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The word I grew up abstinence until you're
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.48,0:33:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,married was the abstinence
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.48,0:33:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,until you're married.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.48,0:33:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I guess that's really old fogey.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.48,0:33:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.48,0:33:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's pick 1955 again.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.48,0:33:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Academia
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.48,0:33:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in 1955
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.48,0:33:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated at 440.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.48,0:33:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,440 is the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.48,0:33:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,level of the colleges recommended
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.48,0:33:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in that book I gave you, the citation.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.48,0:34:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're interested in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.48,0:34:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll put it on the website,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.48,0:34:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the reference to it, ISI,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.48,0:34:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,International Students or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.48,0:34:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, 440
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.12,0:34:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is traditional academia
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.12,0:34:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in which they teach the great books of the western world, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.12,0:34:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Academia
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.12,0:34:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States currently is at 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.12,0:34:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're sending
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.88,0:34:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,your children to become indoctrinated.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.88,0:34:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Marcuse says
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.88,0:34:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the purpose of education is
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.98,0:34:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,indoctrination.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.98,0:34:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Not education,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.98,0:34:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but indoctrination.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.98,0:34:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're spending all that money, tuition money,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.62,0:34:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,with professors.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.62,0:34:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a book called The Professors.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.62,0:34:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,101
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.62,0:34:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,famous professors in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.62,0:34:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,None of them calibrated
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.62,0:34:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,were 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.58,0:34:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,101 professors it's called.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.58,0:34:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget the author of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.58,0:34:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.58,0:34:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If I could see out through these.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.58,0:35:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.40,0:35:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.46,0:35:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.98,0:35:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,at least we know what
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.98,0:35:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,things are going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.23,0:35:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Logical integrity calibrates in the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.23,0:35:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,400s, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.23,0:35:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Sophistry, which is what
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.23,0:35:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,relativism is all about,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.23,0:35:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates 180, 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.23,0:35:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the argument
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.23,0:35:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,between sophistry
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.23,0:35:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and intellectual integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.46,0:35:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,was solved back
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.46,0:35:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,350, 400 BC.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.61,0:35:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Haven't the universities
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.61,0:35:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,heard that yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.73,0:35:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It was solved 450 BC
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.73,0:35:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and recorded throughout history
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.73,0:35:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in Plato's Dialogues.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.53,0:35:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, golly.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.53,0:35:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How can that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.78,0:35:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Logical integrity is the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.78,0:35:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Rhetoric, which was taught
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.78,0:35:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in the One Ancient Rome,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.78,0:35:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,how to present a thing in such a way
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.78,0:35:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,as to influence the audience
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.78,0:35:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,has nothing to do
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.78,0:36:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,with logic, integrity, or truth
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.78,0:36:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.98,0:36:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Traditional morality,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.52,0:36:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that's called traditional
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.52,0:36:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,America, is 490.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.52,0:36:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, currently,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.62,0:36:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Marcuse and all those recommend
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.62,0:36:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that it be replaced by hedonism.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.62,0:36:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hedonism.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.65,0:36:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of life, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.65,0:36:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is self-indulgence,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.74,0:36:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and especially of the erotic variety.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.74,0:36:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hollywood
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.03,0:36:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,movies, remember they had the Hayes office?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.03,0:36:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.03,0:36:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hollywood back in 55 was at 265,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.03,0:36:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and in
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.03,0:36:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,57, it's at 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.03,0:36:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.42,0:36:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayes office,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.64,0:36:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,people here
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.64,0:36:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,don't remember the Hayes office,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.64,0:36:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but in Hollywood, they used to have
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.64,0:36:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,like a review board,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.64,0:36:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and if it was too erotic,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.64,0:36:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,unsuitable for children, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.67,0:36:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,they ruled against it, they had certain rules,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.67,0:36:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,or they at least classified it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.67,0:36:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Mature adults,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.67,0:37:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,children, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.80,0:37:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So they tried to protect,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.80,0:37:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,they didn't restrict free speech, you could still say it,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.80,0:37:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was not recommended
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.80,0:37:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,for children.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.31,0:37:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So Hollywood, the Hayes office
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.31,0:37:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated at 430.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.60,0:37:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,At 430.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.62,0:37:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And porno films still existed,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.62,0:37:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but they were in theaters rated
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.62,0:37:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,triple A, or quadruped four A's.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.62,0:37:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The ad would say
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.62,0:37:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,3AA, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.62,0:37:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and that meant adults only.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.62,0:37:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, don't bring the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.62,0:37:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So freedom still existed, it was separated
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.62,0:37:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,from the main current
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.62,0:37:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,society.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.00,0:37:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayes office.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.00,0:37:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The Sundance Film Festival this year
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.00,0:37:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 165.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.00,0:37:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd have sex with horses
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.80,0:37:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and various interesting things.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.14,0:37:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, a horse never turned me on,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.14,0:37:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I just don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.14,0:38:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.69,0:38:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, to explore deviance
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.69,0:38:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,for its own sake is what it's about,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.69,0:38:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.82,0:38:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And the guy who runs this,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.82,0:38:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,he was going to leave the United States,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.82,0:38:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,what's his name, got reelected,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.82,0:38:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,but he's still hanging out, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.49,0:38:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He was going to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.49,0:38:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.49,0:38:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The classic philosophy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.68,0:38:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,then is, we all know,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.68,0:38:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,440 to 485.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.68,0:38:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The Frankfurt School
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.68,0:38:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates 130 to 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.68,0:38:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what relativism came out of.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.68,0:38:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the Frankfurt
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.68,0:38:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,School, interestingly, was really a
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.68,0:38:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Marxist society.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.16,0:38:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They thought the name Marx would be too
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.16,0:38:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,inflammatory, so they called it
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.16,0:38:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,social theory or
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.16,0:38:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,something.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.34,0:38:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,During the Nazis,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.34,0:38:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,they moved for
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.34,0:38:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,safety's sake. Even though they were
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.34,0:38:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Marxists, they did not move to Russia.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.34,0:39:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They did not move to Russia, interestingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.57,0:39:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they were Marxists,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.57,0:39:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,they didn't go to Russia for safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.57,0:39:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They went to Columbia University in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.57,0:39:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The Frankfurt School
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.66,0:39:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,then was lodged during World War II
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.66,0:39:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,at Columbia University,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.66,0:39:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,who was
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.59,0:39:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,president in 1990.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.59,0:39:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.59,0:39:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,whose faculty has dropped precipitously.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.59,0:39:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it came
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.59,0:39:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to Columbia University.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.59,0:39:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when the coast was clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.59,0:39:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it moved back
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.59,0:39:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to Frankfurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.59,0:39:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.66,0:39:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayes office.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.89,0:39:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy Scouts and Girl Scouts calibrated 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.89,0:39:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, these two organizations
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.89,0:39:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,are anathema.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.42,0:39:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy Scouts and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.68,0:39:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Girl Scouts do everything
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.97,0:39:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that relativism considers
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.97,0:39:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.48,0:39:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Patriotism, integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.48,0:39:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,truth, helpfulness to others,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.48,0:40:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,concern for others.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.67,0:40:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in contrast,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.67,0:40:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what the ACLU supports is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.67,0:40:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,NAMBLA, which calibrates at
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.67,0:40:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,140, which
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.67,0:40:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,legally safeguards the attempts of
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.67,0:40:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,older men to rape
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.67,0:40:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,young boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.28,0:40:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Raping young boys is okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.28,0:40:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Girl Scouts and
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.50,0:40:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy Scouts, not okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.50,0:40:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You see an inversion of what's called
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.98,0:40:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the traditional
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.98,0:40:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Luciferic inversion.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.98,0:40:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Satanic as well as Luciferic.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.98,0:40:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy Scouts and Girl Scouts,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.30,0:40:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which are character
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.30,0:40:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,building, build on honesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.30,0:40:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, a scout is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.30,0:40:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,honest, a scout is hopeful,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.30,0:40:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a scout is eh. And this is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.30,0:40:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the right to seduce and rape young boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.94,0:40:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Classic philosophy as compared to
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.94,0:40:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the Frankfurt School.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.94,0:40:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We have substituted Aristotle
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.94,0:40:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,at 498
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.94,0:40:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,with Marcuse and his
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.94,0:40:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,teaching is called critical theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.94,0:41:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Critical theory at
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.94,0:41:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,140 to 150. And I read
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.94,0:41:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you some of the dictums of critical theory
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.94,0:41:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.94,0:41:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Sophocles at
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.94,0:41:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,465.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.04,0:41:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Relativistic philosophy 130
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.04,0:41:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.14,0:41:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Huang Po calibrated
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.62,0:41:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,960. Oh yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.62,0:41:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,here he is, 960.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.65,0:41:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Dawkins who feels that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.65,0:41:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, religion should be banned
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.65,0:41:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.90,0:41:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,190. So
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.16,0:41:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,what relativism is doing is
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.16,0:41:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,asking us to move from the level
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.16,0:41:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 400s, 500s,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.16,0:41:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,live 300s down to
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.16,0:41:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,less than 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.74,0:41:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore that would explain why when we
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.74,0:41:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.86,0:41:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level of the western world
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.86,0:41:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we see that it's going down.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.86,0:41:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that it's going down.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.02,0:41:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I had thought, even
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.02,0:41:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the beginning lectures we gave here,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.02,0:41:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that consciousness level man was
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.02,0:42:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,going to go up and keep going up like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.02,0:42:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it turned
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.02,0:42:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,over and came down.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.02,0:42:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So it could be the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.02,0:42:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic purpose of this life, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.02,0:42:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is such that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.12,0:42:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we have the options and it may be
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.12,0:42:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's going to be waves of
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.12,0:42:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,fluctuation in which mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.41,0:42:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,overall rises
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.41,0:42:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and then falls, you know. I don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.41,0:42:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,because I haven't been
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.41,0:42:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,alive for that many
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.41,0:42:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,millions years.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.41,0:42:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Classic, classic.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.41,0:42:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Aristotle and Soplites,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.41,0:42:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,alright. Huang Po versus
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.41,0:42:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Richard Dawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.76,0:42:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Dawkins. People of the Lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.76,0:42:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,M. Scott Peck
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.76,0:42:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,at 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.08,0:42:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,M. Scott Peck was a psychiatrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.08,0:42:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He compared conspiracy theories
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.08,0:42:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and paranoia, you know, nutty
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.08,0:42:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,professors, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.08,0:42:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now M. Scott Peck was a psychiatrist
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.08,0:42:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's a very interesting book.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.08,0:42:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a bestseller some years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.08,0:42:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people here have read People of the Lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.08,0:42:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh good, so there's
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.08,0:43:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,familiarity.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.34,0:43:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I just rediscovered
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.34,0:43:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that book. I'd totally forgotten about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.34,0:43:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But he concluded
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.50,0:43:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that the basis of evil
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.50,0:43:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,was narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.50,0:43:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The refusal to grant that there's
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.50,0:43:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,anything greater than yourself or
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.50,0:43:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,your own ego, even
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.66,0:43:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,if it's your neighborhood
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.66,0:43:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,school.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.66,0:43:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That evil is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.01,0:43:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,really nothing but unabashed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.01,0:43:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,totally naked narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.01,0:43:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that was
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.26,0:43:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting. So here he is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.39,0:43:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,a psychiatrist and after listening to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.39,0:43:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,some people for some years
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.39,0:43:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,he decided basically they weren't sick
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.39,0:43:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,they were just evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.39,0:43:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well that was not exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.39,0:43:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,a popular opinion in the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.39,0:43:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,psychiatric field. Evil
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.39,0:43:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and goodness didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.39,0:43:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,enter into it, you know. So I thought
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.55,0:43:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it was quite brave of him to write that
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.55,0:43:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's written a couple other books
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.55,0:43:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I think confirming the same idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.55,0:43:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But the fact that he identified narcissism
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.55,0:44:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,as the core of it all
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.55,0:44:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought was quite interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.55,0:44:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.74,0:44:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you see modernism
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.74,0:44:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is 400.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.86,0:44:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Modernism means
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.09,0:44:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,oh some of my favorite cars
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.09,0:44:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,were back in the 30's. They came out as
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.09,0:44:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,streamlined. Remember the first
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.09,0:44:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,streamlined cars? I mean they were terrific
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.09,0:44:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,looking, the collector's items.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.09,0:44:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean they were sleek, gorgeous looking cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.09,0:44:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course they replaced
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.09,0:44:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the old model A4's.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.09,0:44:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So suddenly when a sleek car came
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.09,0:44:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,out it knocked me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.25,0:44:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,When I saw the first streamlined
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.25,0:44:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,car. So that was
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.25,0:44:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,modernism was really
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.25,0:44:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,modern design in architecture
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.25,0:44:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and in automotive
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.25,0:44:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,design and refrigerators
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.25,0:44:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.31,0:44:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So modernism is
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.31,0:44:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,400. Post
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.41,0:44:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,modernism however is only
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.41,0:44:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,180. So from
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.41,0:44:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,modernism it then fell
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.41,0:44:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,down.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.44,0:45:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Intellectual morons
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.33,0:45:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,oh yes I mentioned that book
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.33,0:45:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,this morning because a lot of the people were quoting
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.33,0:45:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a very interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.33,0:45:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,book. I mean it could be boring
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.33,0:45:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're not interested in the subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.68,0:45:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But the question is how could such a
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.68,0:45:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,tremendous reversal
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.84,0:45:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,180 occur?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.84,0:45:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,How could it possibly occur?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.90,0:45:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And this
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.90,0:45:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,gives you the personal
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.90,0:45:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,lives of these various people
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.90,0:45:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and I found it was very
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.90,0:45:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,educational just like M. Scott
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.90,0:45:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Blake's book is
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.90,0:45:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,educational. Intellectual morons.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.90,0:45:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,U.S. society in
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.13,0:45:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,2007 is
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.13,0:45:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,currently at
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.13,0:45:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,421.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.38,0:45:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a day or two ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.64,0:45:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The world overall right now comes out
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.64,0:45:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,at 205.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.83,0:45:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now they had both been higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.83,0:45:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll remember from our lectures a couple
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.83,0:45:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.90,0:46:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's come down just about
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.90,0:46:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,four points just in the last couple
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.90,0:46:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of years. I suppose
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.90,0:46:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,from the impact of the two things that
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.90,0:46:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we're talking about today.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.92,0:46:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Cable news calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.92,0:46:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,410 to 440. That's higher than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.92,0:46:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh the Huffington
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.21,0:46:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Post, MySpace, YouTube
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.21,0:46:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is at 140.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.21,0:46:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Although we castigate the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.21,0:46:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,announcers
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.21,0:46:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,they do have a certain amount of credibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.21,0:46:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the cable news.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.21,0:46:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay so we'll go to the next
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.21,0:46:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,one. I just wanted to
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.33,0:46:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,put that in because
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.74,0:46:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the blogger
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.74,0:46:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,land, whatever they call it,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.74,0:46:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,www internet computer
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.74,0:46:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,world zone
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.06,0:46:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,thing is
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.29,0:46:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,has quite a detrimental
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.29,0:46:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,effect apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.74,0:46:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just picked up, I never heard
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.74,0:46:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of it before but I was on TV the other day
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.74,0:46:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and I said
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.74,0:47:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,what does that calibrate at? What are people
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.74,0:47:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at for their political viewpoints?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.74,0:47:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And that it's
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.74,0:47:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that low. It's sort of shocking.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.28,0:47:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The essence
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.28,0:47:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,here we have, man has
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.54,0:47:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the capacity for reason
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.54,0:47:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,his prefrontal cortex, his intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.54,0:47:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So his intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.54,0:47:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,really starts about 200
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.54,0:47:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and then continues on up.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.63,0:47:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,See animals have intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.63,0:47:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,They have intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.79,0:47:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So reality
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.79,0:47:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,truth and essence
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.79,0:47:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,really requires the prefrontal
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.79,0:47:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,cortex which is not really too
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.79,0:47:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,operative until you get to 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.02,0:47:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Relativism which is based on
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.02,0:47:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,appearance and illusion
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.18,0:47:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on the physiology
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.18,0:47:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of the other side of the brain
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.18,0:47:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,which is called the limbic
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.18,0:47:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,system operating out
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.18,0:47:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of the amygdala which is
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.18,0:47:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,emotionalized
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.18,0:47:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.21,0:48:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So how are we
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.94,0:48:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,going to talk people who think with a
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.94,0:48:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,different part of their brain
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.94,0:48:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,into seeing things the way
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.94,0:48:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we see them? Maybe we're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.54,0:48:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Laughter
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.54,0:48:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's up to evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.54,0:48:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's up to
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.54,0:48:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic merit.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.54,0:48:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's up to
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.82,0:48:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,something other than political persuasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.82,0:48:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.46,0:48:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,after what we've learned this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.46,0:48:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I would try to buy these people out.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.46,0:48:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Laughter
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.76,0:48:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll do anything for money.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.18,0:48:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not give up war for money?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.88,0:48:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Give them money for everybody they don't kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.88,0:48:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Discretion then
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.32,0:48:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is 375.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.64,0:48:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Vilification and desecration
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.64,0:48:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,are 120.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.93,0:48:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,To disagree
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.54,0:48:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.54,0:49:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,go to vilification
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.54,0:49:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and desecration.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.54,0:49:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to drop way down to
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.54,0:49:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,120 or 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.82,0:49:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to curse America
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.82,0:49:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,or curse Americans.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.82,0:49:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You can just totally
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.82,0:49:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,disagree and just say
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.82,0:49:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe I would do it
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.82,0:49:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.07,0:49:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The Statue of Liberty
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.07,0:49:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,like patriotism and the flag and other things
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.07,0:49:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 500
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.07,0:49:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,because its energy
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.07,0:49:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is more than just its physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.07,0:49:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The MMS plane
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.55,0:49:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,set up calibrates at 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.55,0:49:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So this
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.55,0:49:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,incident is trying to hide
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.55,0:49:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,under the cloak of
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.81,0:49:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,freedom and liberty.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.29,0:49:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We will imitate
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.29,0:49:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly how plane
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.29,0:49:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,hijackers operate
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.29,0:49:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,right down to the last iota.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.29,0:49:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And then if we get
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.29,0:49:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,a response. So this was a fake
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.29,0:49:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,set up. This was staged.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.29,0:49:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we will threaten to sue.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.29,0:50:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So this was a set up
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.35,0:50:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,which under the cover of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.35,0:50:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,relativism
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.83,0:50:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,they get away with.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.02,0:50:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But calling a spade a spade
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.02,0:50:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it was very obvious
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.02,0:50:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,what was going on to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.02,0:50:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact they went to extremes
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.02,0:50:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to ask for seatbelt extenders.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.02,0:50:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So they imitated exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.02,0:50:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,what the hijackers
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.02,0:50:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,had done.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.02,0:50:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.24,0:50:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,what we are up against
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.24,0:50:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is people that are more crafty
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.24,0:50:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,more crafty
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.24,0:50:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,than we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.24,0:50:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We are still naive babes
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.24,0:50:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.37,0:50:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,People think that had to do with religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.37,0:50:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got nothing to do with religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.37,0:50:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.78,0:50:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.78,0:50:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Abstract thought you see
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.94,0:50:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is at 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.94,0:50:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Concrete thinking is at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.94,0:50:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,190.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.94,0:50:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So this level of thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.52,0:51:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in the context
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.52,0:51:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are being set up
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.52,0:51:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you just fell right into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.52,0:51:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They set it up and you fell right in.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.16,0:51:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you don't get the abstract
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.16,0:51:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.16,0:51:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The abstract thought is 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.16,0:51:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Concrete thinking is 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.16,0:51:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.15,0:51:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning itself
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.15,0:51:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is where relativism
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.15,0:51:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,really falls down.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.15,0:51:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It says nothing means anything
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.15,0:51:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,except what I say it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.15,0:51:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's totally narcissistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.15,0:51:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So it says
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.28,0:51:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to serve
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.28,0:51:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,what anything means
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.28,0:51:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because it'll mean what I want it to mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.28,0:51:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be what I want it to mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.34,0:51:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the ultimate of narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.34,0:51:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And you know
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.34,0:51:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,from Lewis Carroll's
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.66,0:51:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Looking Glass
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.66,0:51:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget who it is
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.70,0:51:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the rabbit or the mad hatter
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.70,0:51:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it says a word means
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.70,0:51:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,what I mean it to mean
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.56,0:51:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing more and nothing less.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.56,0:52:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's today's modernism.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.56,0:52:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing more and nothing less.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.56,0:52:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Because nothing has any intrinsic
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.56,0:52:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,essence or meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.56,0:52:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore I can label it
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.56,0:52:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,any way I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.56,0:52:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So the victory of
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.01,0:52:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,subjectivism over being objective.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.01,0:52:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Higher mind is
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.23,0:52:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,a 275 and lower mind
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.23,0:52:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 155.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.23,0:52:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,These are different energy
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.23,0:52:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,constellations.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.23,0:52:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Actual different energy constellations.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.68,0:52:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,To be friendly calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.68,0:52:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,at 255.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.78,0:52:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.78,0:52:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,my kitty Bootsy
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.83,0:52:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Bootsy's overly friendly actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.83,0:52:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He threw himself all over you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.83,0:52:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 255
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.83,0:52:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and hostile is at 125.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.83,0:52:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.83,0:52:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,why should we be hostile?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.83,0:52:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should we give up friendliness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.83,0:52:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,for hostility?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.83,0:52:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,To stand up for the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.83,0:52:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.96,0:53:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, why is it so high?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.96,0:53:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Because truth itself is only in the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.96,0:53:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.96,0:53:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But to stand up for the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.96,0:53:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is different than quoting the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.96,0:53:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,500
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.09,0:53:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,then takes
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.09,0:53:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,a higher degree of integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.09,0:53:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,To stand up for the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.38,0:53:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,willing to stand up
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.38,0:53:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and be counted.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.66,0:53:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That does not however mean to be foolish
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.66,0:53:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and indiscreet.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.70,0:53:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,To stand up for the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.27,0:53:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you see is not combative.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.27,0:53:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that you stand
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.27,0:53:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for what you believe in.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.27,0:53:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You stand up for the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.27,0:53:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and say in my viewpoint
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.27,0:53:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,America is taking the wrong direction
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.27,0:53:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is why.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.27,0:53:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing wrong with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.27,0:53:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So tolerance then
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.27,0:53:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Marcuse
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.37,0:53:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,political meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.37,0:53:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.37,0:53:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's current political usage
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.37,0:53:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,when they talk about tolerance
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.37,0:53:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.72,0:54:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It means tolerance
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.23,0:54:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to stand
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.54,0:54:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,for what you politically believe in
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.54,0:54:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and to try to destroy
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.54,0:54:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you do not.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.54,0:54:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So tolerance does not mean
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.54,0:54:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,so when people hear tolerance
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.54,0:54:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,they haven't read Marcuse's
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.54,0:54:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,definition of tolerance.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.54,0:54:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Marcuse says tolerance means
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.54,0:54:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,tolerance for the left
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.54,0:54:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and intolerance to everything on the right
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.54,0:54:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,which should be destroyed and attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.54,0:54:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has no rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.54,0:54:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's the complete opposite of free speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.54,0:54:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're selling intolerance
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.54,0:54:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,based on freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.66,0:54:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the purpose of the world anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.66,0:54:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it up to us to run out there
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.66,0:54:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and try and save it?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.73,0:54:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go burning all Marcuse's books?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.73,0:54:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we panic because we see
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.73,0:54:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of consciousness of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.73,0:54:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,went up and now it's coming down again?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.76,0:54:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the world our responsibility?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.76,0:55:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well we say
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.98,0:55:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the question of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.98,0:55:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the world
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.98,0:55:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,as a karmic expression?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.05,0:55:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the world
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.05,0:55:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of infinite karmic potentiality?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.05,0:55:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That calibrates at 575.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.05,0:55:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,540 is above
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.05,0:55:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.05,0:55:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,570 is sainthood.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.05,0:55:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,To see this
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.24,0:55:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,as a world of karmic expression
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.24,0:55:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and the enfoldment of potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.24,0:55:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of the human evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.24,0:55:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is 575.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.91,0:55:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,To see the world as unfair
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.91,0:55:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.23,0:55:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you would have to define
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.23,0:55:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,what you mean by unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.23,0:55:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's a perfect karmic enfoldment
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.49,0:55:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,then the world is completely fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.49,0:55:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Human life is completely fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.49,0:55:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if we have permission
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.58,0:55:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to ask that.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.58,0:55:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Human life is completely
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.97,0:55:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and totally karmically fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.97,0:55:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.97,0:55:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's give up all the blubbering.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.88,0:56:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor us.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.33,0:56:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.87,0:56:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel sorry for us poor humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.03,0:56:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I think being human
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.03,0:56:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.12,0:56:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It really is difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.12,0:56:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,By handling and facing
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.12,0:56:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and owning that difficulty
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.12,0:56:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you earn karmic merit.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.12,0:56:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't get into heaven
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.12,0:56:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.50,0:56:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A few years
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.50,0:56:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in the lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.50,0:56:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,World as karmic expression
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.89,0:56:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is 575.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.89,0:56:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So the world is not unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.89,0:56:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Not unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.21,0:56:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't say it's fair
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.21,0:56:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,nor that it's unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.21,0:56:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.21,0:56:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's neither fair nor unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.21,0:56:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore it depends on
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.21,0:56:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,how you experience it as yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.37,0:56:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If you see the world
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.37,0:57:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,as maximum karmic opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.37,0:57:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that's 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.37,0:57:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,600 this world is a world.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.37,0:57:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is what the Buddha taught.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.37,0:57:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The world said lucky it is
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.53,0:57:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to be born a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.53,0:57:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucky it is to be born a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.53,0:57:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Even luckier yet to have heard
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.53,0:57:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Buddha and her enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.82,0:57:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Buddha said
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.82,0:57:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the world is a minority
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.82,0:57:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and that calibrates at 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.84,0:57:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's enemies, the enemies of truth
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.84,0:57:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,say the world is exploitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.84,0:57:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,180.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.25,0:57:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is exploitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.25,0:57:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.25,0:57:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is unjust.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.34,0:57:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a world of oppression.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.69,0:57:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the victim mentality.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.78,0:57:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That the world is exploitive now
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.78,0:57:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,means that the minority
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.78,0:57:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is always being exploited
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.78,0:57:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,by the majority.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.78,0:57:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So Marxism
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.82,0:57:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,sees that minorities
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.82,0:57:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,are all victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.82,0:58:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So Marcuse taught
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.58,0:58:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that instead of having it industrial
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.58,0:58:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and has anything to do
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.58,0:58:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,with capital and all
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.58,0:58:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,what you do is say that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.58,0:58:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,what you do is you say that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.08,0:58:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the minority is always being exploited
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.08,0:58:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,by the majority.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.08,0:58:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.88,0:58:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the majority can never be right
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.88,0:58:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,from the viewpoint of Marcuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.39,0:58:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You instantly become wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.39,0:58:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,if you become the majority.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.39,0:58:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the exploiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.39,0:58:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Every minority then becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.46,0:58:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,a victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.38,0:58:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Old psychiatrists
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.18,0:58:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,are victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.18,0:58:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Old white psychiatrists
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.83,0:58:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,are super victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.62,0:58:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So anything can be colored
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.62,0:58:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,with whatever kind of paint
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.62,0:58:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you wish to spray it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.62,0:58:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I prefer to see it
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.91,0:59:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,as a world of maximum
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.91,0:59:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.91,0:59:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you're grateful
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.91,0:59:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,for the karmic opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.91,0:59:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to undo negative karma
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.91,0:59:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and create positive karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.52,0:59:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The impact of traditional
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.52,0:59:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,religion on US society
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.52,0:59:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.52,0:59:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The total impact
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.58,0:59:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of traditional religion
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.58,0:59:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,ethics, morality,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.65,0:59:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,answerability,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.65,0:59:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,accountability, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.00,0:59:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.00,0:59:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Secularism on the other hand
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.00,0:59:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.00,0:59:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In secularism you're not accountable
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.00,0:59:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for what is wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.00,0:59:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it's somebody's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.71,0:59:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We did money trumps peace
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.71,0:59:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and now we have a secret
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.71,0:59:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that nobody in the world knows
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.48,0:59:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,except us.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.48,0:59:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up the peace parades
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.48,0:59:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and get some money
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.48,1:00:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and buy us some peace
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.30,1:00:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,around here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.30,1:00:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to test out
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.30,1:00:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the Pope's declaration.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.65,1:00:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In non-linear dynamics
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.13,1:00:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a term
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.13,1:00:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,called iteration.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.13,1:00:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It means if
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.45,1:00:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,even in the 26th decimal point
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.45,1:00:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you're off one digit
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.45,1:00:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,repeated enough time
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.45,1:00:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,it will eventually
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.45,1:00:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,reverse the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.12,1:00:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,An error in the 26th digit
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.12,1:00:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,which was in some computer
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.12,1:00:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I mentioned it in previous lectures
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.12,1:00:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,some computer program
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.12,1:00:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,or something I forget
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.47,1:00:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,some chip or something
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.47,1:00:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,well they figured 26 decimals out
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.47,1:00:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody's ever going to get that far
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.47,1:00:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,on a daily use basis.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.63,1:00:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But they did
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.50,1:00:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because so iteration means
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.50,1:00:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that the slightest error
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.50,1:00:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,slightest error
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.50,1:00:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,almost imperceptible error
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.62,1:00:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,if repeated often enough
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.62,1:01:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,will eventually have a
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.62,1:01:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,profound effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.98,1:01:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're a little bit
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.98,1:01:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,a little bit a little bit
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.98,1:01:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly you're way off.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.26,1:01:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So the destruction
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.65,1:01:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of society by iteration
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.65,1:01:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.68,1:01:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a confidence level of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.68,1:01:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.09,1:01:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is merely confirming
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.09,1:01:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,what the Pope said.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.22,1:01:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.22,1:01:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,chipping away at truth
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.22,1:01:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,teaching post-modernism
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.31,1:01:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,teaching religious concepts
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.31,1:01:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that are really more satanic
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.31,1:01:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and luciferic than logical.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.66,1:01:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.66,1:01:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,by repetition
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.66,1:01:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,by repetition
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.66,1:01:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,by iteration
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.07,1:01:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,constant repetition
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.07,1:01:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's my concern about
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.36,1:01:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,this little politician
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.36,1:01:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,gives this little twist
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.36,1:01:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,this little advertisement
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.36,1:02:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,gives this little twist
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.36,1:02:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,this photograph
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.36,1:02:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,upstages the central figure
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.36,1:02:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,whose message it is
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.36,1:02:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to get across
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.81,1:02:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,subtly subtly subtly
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.81,1:02:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,round the clock
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.81,1:02:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,round the clock
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.81,1:02:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,seven days a week
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.81,1:02:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,year in and year out
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.58,1:02:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,by iteration
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.02,1:02:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to the human capacity
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.54,1:02:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern illusion
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.54,1:02:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,from reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.66,1:02:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So my only complaint
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.66,1:02:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,or worry about it
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.21,1:02:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,as a physician
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.21,1:02:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is that by iteration
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.69,1:02:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the human capacity
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.69,1:02:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern truth
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.69,1:02:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.69,1:02:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern the essence of truth
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.69,1:02:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is injured.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.83,1:02:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.28,1:02:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's the damage to the human psyche
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.28,1:02:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,about which
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.28,1:02:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm concerned
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.21,1:03:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,not the falsehood itself
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.21,1:03:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,because falsehood comes and goes
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.78,1:03:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but the innate capacity
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.78,1:03:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of the human mind
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.88,1:03:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so the programming that goes on
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.88,1:03:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in academia for instance
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.88,1:03:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to me
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.91,1:03:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't resent the falsehood of it
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.07,1:03:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but the fact that their capacity
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.07,1:03:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.14,1:03:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,recognize truth
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.52,1:03:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,when they hear it
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.52,1:03:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,has been injured
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.38,1:03:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's why I want my tuition back
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.38,1:03:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.55,1:03:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that they can't jump
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.22,1:03:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,various hoops anymore
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.22,1:03:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but that their legs
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.38,1:03:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,are no longer strong enough
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.38,1:03:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to take them over the barriers
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.38,1:03:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,their mental
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.76,1:03:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,anatomy and capacity
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.76,1:03:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I see it as urgent
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.76,1:03:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,now
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.76,1:03:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the repair of all that
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.76,1:03:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the repair
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.30,1:04:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.75,1:04:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it means that each and every one of us
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.75,1:04:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,tries to be as integrous as they can
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.75,1:04:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,within their own domain
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.75,1:04:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,within their own life
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.33,1:04:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,because the energy that you put out
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.33,1:04:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,as you can see from the last slide
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.33,1:04:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,where's the last slide
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.46,1:04:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,affects others
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.46,1:04:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,just by that which you are
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.46,1:04:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,see
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.67,1:04:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,just that which you are
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.12,1:04:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to merely be friendly
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.12,1:04:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is 255
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.12,1:04:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.70,1:04:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,one person being friendly
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.70,1:04:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is more powerful
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.70,1:04:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,than five people being nasty
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.70,1:04:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so the way to offset it
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.82,1:04:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is not to make an enemy out of it
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.82,1:04:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and attack it
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.82,1:04:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's right
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.82,1:04:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,being seduced to fall into the trap
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.89,1:04:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,by each one of us
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.89,1:04:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,by being as loving as we can
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.05,1:04:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,as loving
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.62,1:04:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,as helpful
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.75,1:04:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,as truthful
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.75,1:05:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,as honest
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.75,1:05:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.75,1:05:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,by our own integrity then
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.75,1:05:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,as we've said before
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.75,1:05:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,each one of us
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.75,1:05:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is like the sea
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.75,1:05:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and as the level of the sea rises
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.75,1:05:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it lifts all the ships
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.98,1:05:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,ships on the sea
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.98,1:05:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,so the way to help with this situation
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.98,1:05:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is not by attacking falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.98,1:05:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,not by attacking falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.07,1:05:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but instead becoming the fullest
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.07,1:05:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfillment and development
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.07,1:05:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and expression
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.07,1:05:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of your own spiritual potentiality
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.26,1:05:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,now a group like this
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.22,1:05:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,curiously enough
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.22,1:05:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,can be the tail
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.22,1:05:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that wags the dog
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.59,1:05:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,we have permission to ask this
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.39,1:05:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,this group alone already
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.03,1:05:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,affects the consciousness of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.03,1:05:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,this group alone
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.42,1:05:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,affects favorably
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.42,1:05:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness of all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.42,1:06:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,why?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.38,1:06:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is rare
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.38,1:06:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it's unique
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.38,1:06:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you hardly get this many people
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.38,1:06:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,together of a higher level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.38,1:06:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere in this world
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.38,1:06:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,much less with the awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.41,1:06:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of how to discern truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.41,1:06:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and conscious awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.41,1:06:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.41,1:06:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and the part it plays
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.86,1:06:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,from evolution etc
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.02,1:06:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,so this group
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.02,1:06:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.02,1:06:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which they
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.02,1:06:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,just that which they are
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.02,1:06:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,helps uplift all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.02,1:06:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,this group alone
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.02,1:06:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,this group alone
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.02,1:06:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,uplifts the consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.56,1:06:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.33,1:06:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want you to respect
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.78,1:06:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the innate
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.87,1:06:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of innate divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.87,1:06:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,within you
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.87,1:06:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't you as a person
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.87,1:06:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,it's that which acknowledges and reflects
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.87,1:06:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.19,1:07:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,already uplifts
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.54,1:07:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.98,1:07:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,so you didn't exactly
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.98,1:07:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,waste Saturday afternoon
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.58,1:07:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so the contribution
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.99,1:07:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you see is not what you do
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.99,1:07:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that's why I'm not
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.99,1:07:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,enthused about peace parades and all
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.99,1:07:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,because they just set up oppositional
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.99,1:07:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and the cops and the hoses and the dogs and all
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.89,1:07:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no opposition
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.11,1:07:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to you becoming the fullest
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.11,1:07:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,expression of your own potential
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.11,1:07:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no opposition to that
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.11,1:07:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you have no enemies
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.52,1:07:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody can do anything about it
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.22,1:07:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you see how beautiful that is
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.22,1:07:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,so every time you look at
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.95,1:07:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the little bug and you say
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.95,1:07:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,oh little bug look at him
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.98,1:07:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,his arms are leaning on his back
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.98,1:07:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and say oh that little bug
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.98,1:07:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you turn him over
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.24,1:08:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you just change the world
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.24,1:08:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you just change the world
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.46,1:08:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,he just says bugs
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.46,1:08:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,well I hate them
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.50,1:08:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and walks on
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.50,1:08:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,oh poor little bugs
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.26,1:08:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.47,1:08:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that capacity to be compassionate
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.47,1:08:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to identify
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.47,1:08:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and see the divinity of all
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.47,1:08:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the innate divinity of all of life
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.47,1:08:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,then you begin to recognize it
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.47,1:08:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in all that exists
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.47,1:08:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're walking through the woods
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.47,1:08:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and you look out and you see the radiance
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.47,1:08:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,oh I better not look in there
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.89,1:08:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the radiance
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.14,1:08:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of nature
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.14,1:08:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you see divinity shining forth
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.14,1:08:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,as the glory of the perfection
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.14,1:08:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of all creation
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.24,1:08:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,because the creator is not different than that
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.24,1:08:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the created
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.24,1:08:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the creator is within creation
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.24,1:08:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,ever present
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.24,1:08:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,ever evolving
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.24,1:08:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see the divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.24,1:09:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of all creation
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.58,1:09:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,first you see
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.41,1:09:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,through lovingness
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.41,1:09:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you appreciate its beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.57,1:09:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,its incredible beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.57,1:09:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly one day
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.57,1:09:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you see a tree
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.57,1:09:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,as you've never seen a tree before
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.57,1:09:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,stunning perfection
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.57,1:09:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,stands there radiating out
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.57,1:09:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the perfection of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.45,1:09:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.45,1:09:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the radiance of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.63,1:09:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to shine forth
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.63,1:09:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,as all existence
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.63,1:09:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.14,1:09:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,your own existence
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.14,1:09:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is a reflection
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.14,1:09:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of divinity within yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.14,1:09:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you also reflect divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.43,1:09:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to a non-human
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.43,1:09:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at you
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.43,1:09:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,they would fall back in wonderment
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.53,1:09:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,at the energy that radiates forth from you
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.53,1:09:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the animal feels the human
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.53,1:10:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,coming down the path
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.53,1:10:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,he already picks up the radiation
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.53,1:10:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and the energy of it
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.53,1:10:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's friendly or not
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.88,1:10:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so to become
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.88,1:10:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the highest greatest fulfillment
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.88,1:10:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that we can become
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.91,1:10:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.91,1:10:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,in maximum service
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.91,1:10:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to God
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.07,1:10:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to your fellow man
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.07,1:10:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to life
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.46,1:10:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to the planet
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.22,1:10:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to the animal kingdom
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.22,1:10:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to nature
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.38,1:10:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the best environmental act you can perform
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.38,1:10:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be the perfection of that which you are
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.42,1:10:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to fulfill that potentiality
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.15,1:10:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in doing that
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.15,1:10:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's the way to worship God
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.15,1:10:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,who is probably sick and tired of bills
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.15,1:10:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,incense kneeling
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.15,1:10:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,drapery holy drapery
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.15,1:10:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,give me the holy drapery
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.15,1:10:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a couple centuries of that
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.42,1:10:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,water some flowers
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.42,1:11:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,do something
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.24,1:11:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.27,1:11:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the message that I just conveyed
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.27,1:11:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.27,1:11:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the message I just conveyed
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.78,1:11:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.78,1:11:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Calvary is over 750
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.91,1:11:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,740
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.91,1:11:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,745
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.91,1:11:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,740 is good enough for a Saturday afternoon
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.35,1:11:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth of what I just said
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.35,1:11:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the reason I wanted to calibrate it
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.35,1:11:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just the recognition
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.35,1:11:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of a very profound truth
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.35,1:11:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and the more you become the mystic
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.35,1:11:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and less the religionist
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.35,1:11:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the more these things become very obvious
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.35,1:11:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that the radiance
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.51,1:11:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which you are
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.51,1:11:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to the world
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.51,1:11:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is the greatest gift you can give the world
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.70,1:11:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to be all that I can be to this world
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.70,1:11:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,through thee oh Lord
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.56,1:11:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,through thy glory
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.23,1:12:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.79,1:12:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,now
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.89,1:12:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we can stop early did we
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.17,1:12:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we can stop early
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.17,1:12:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,well we're going to break and then we're going to have
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.17,1:12:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,what after that
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.20,1:12:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to have questions and answers
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.76,1:12:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,if you have questions and books
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.42,1:12:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,alright now
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.42,1:12:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,before we break
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.42,1:12:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,has anybody got a question of general interest
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.42,1:12:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to the population
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.42,1:12:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,not about you and your mother-in-law
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.78,1:12:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,any kind of a general question
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.54,1:12:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,having to do with the theory
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.54,1:12:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the essence of what we spoke about today
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.54,1:12:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,pertinent to it yes
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.91,1:12:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,no
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.58,1:13:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because each one
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.63,1:13:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is there to serve their own
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.63,1:13:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,constituency
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.79,1:13:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,if a country sends me and pays my way
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.79,1:13:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to get a better deal for hog farmers
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.79,1:13:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't go back
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.79,1:13:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that I've given away hog farming
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.79,1:13:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Chinese or something
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.79,1:13:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to come back that I got a deal
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.79,1:13:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and how much did it cost
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.79,1:13:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's a marketplace
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.79,1:13:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,a wheeler dealer it's a bazaar
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.79,1:13:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the UN is a bazaar
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.79,1:13:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,a trading bazaar political favors financial favors
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.82,1:13:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,status favors
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.82,1:13:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,good mentions etc
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.95,1:13:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,it can only be what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.95,1:13:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not saying it's bad
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.95,1:13:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just that I think people put
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.95,1:13:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,false hope in those things
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.95,1:13:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,because it sounds utopian
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.95,1:13:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,utopian
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.95,1:13:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,we tried the League of Nations
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.95,1:13:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and that ended up as World War I
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.02,1:13:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,now we have
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.37,1:13:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,World War II
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.37,1:13:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,it just doesn't work
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.37,1:13:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,it's idealistic but not practical
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.37,1:14:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.67,1:14:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what you say about an apologist
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.67,1:14:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,an apologist and being forgiving
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.67,1:14:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,she wants to know the difference between
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.93,1:14:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,well an apologist makes excuses
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.93,1:14:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,for evil and thereby joins it karmically
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.92,1:14:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you can forgive evil because they know
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.92,1:14:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,not what they do no problem
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.92,1:14:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but to forgive it is different
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.05,1:14:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,than being an apologist
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.05,1:14:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're an apologist
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.05,1:14:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you take on part of the karma
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.05,1:14:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,if you say you know
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.21,1:14:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the Nazi invasion of Europe is okay
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.21,1:14:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,then you take on
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.04,1:14:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the karma
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.04,1:14:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,yes
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.32,1:14:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bill of Rights
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.06,1:14:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bill of Rights is the constitutional
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.06,1:14:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,guarantee of equality
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.06,1:14:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and especially also between the sexes
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.06,1:15:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,shiara is a
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.38,1:15:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,completely different thing
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.38,1:15:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,shiara has to do with certain
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.38,1:15:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,belief systems primarily political
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.38,1:15:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize the Koran is
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.38,1:15:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,90% political
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.38,1:15:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,has very little to do with religion
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.38,1:15:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,has to do with the rights of various subgroups
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.38,1:15:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,political groups, physicians, men, women
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.38,1:15:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.61,1:15:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the Koran divides the world into
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.61,1:15:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,two houses
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.64,1:15:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the house of Islam
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.93,1:15:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and the house of war
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.93,1:15:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you believe the way they do
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.93,1:15:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,then you're in the house of Islam
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.93,1:15:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you don't believe the way they do
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.93,1:15:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,then you're in the house of war
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.99,1:15:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the United States is in the house of war
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.66,1:15:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,yes
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.80,1:16:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,who is an eagle scout
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.63,1:16:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,it has to do with being
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.63,1:16:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a scout master
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.63,1:16:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,not a scout
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.63,1:16:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you see
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.63,1:16:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is an authority position
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.82,1:16:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the history of people with that kind of disorder
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.82,1:16:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is not too good with young children
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.82,1:16:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself went through it myself
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.82,1:16:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,so I didn't read this out of a book
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.75,1:16:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,so somebody can be very
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.75,1:16:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,teach Sunday school
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.82,1:16:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and crawl you into
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.65,1:16:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,which you can do nothing
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.65,1:16:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because the person is bigger, older, stronger
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.65,1:16:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and has authority and you're nobody
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.65,1:16:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's taking them out of that
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.65,1:16:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,position
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.71,1:16:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,which is seductive
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.71,1:16:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the scout master himself
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.71,1:16:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,he now knows that he has available
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.71,1:16:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,all these kids
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.74,1:17:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're saying it's doubtful
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.74,1:17:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,whether that person would be able to handle it
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.61,1:17:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't want the legal liability
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.61,1:17:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't want to be running a kindergarten
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.93,1:17:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and knowingly hire somebody
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.93,1:17:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,who is known to violate the
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.93,1:17:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,rights of children
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.98,1:17:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know I don't get the question
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.80,1:17:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,there's just two different
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.83,1:17:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,realms of integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.83,1:17:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy Scouts and all that
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.83,1:17:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is about 440, 460
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.09,1:17:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and ACLU is about 130
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.09,1:17:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it says you know
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.09,1:17:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you know they don't even
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.86,1:17:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if they really know what they defend
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.86,1:17:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,do they know what it is to be a child
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.86,1:17:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,held down by a big powerful strong
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.86,1:17:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,person and have your anus ripped
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.86,1:18:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you can't hold your feces
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.86,1:18:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and you gotta go see the doctor
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.86,1:18:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're too ashamed to tell your mother
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.40,1:18:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,they have no idea what they're talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.69,1:18:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what they call an ideologist
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.69,1:18:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,an ideologue
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.88,1:18:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,will tell you
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.20,1:18:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's not the reality
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.51,1:18:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that any boy has been in the reality
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.51,1:18:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to get
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.63,1:18:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't tell you how many times passes were made at me
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.20,1:18:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not a political issue
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.19,1:18:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the last time a pass was made at me was
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.19,1:18:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,shall we tell them
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.24,1:18:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,huh
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.66,1:18:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,this will be the last story
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.66,1:18:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're going to bring
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.12,1:18:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to San Francisco to see my favorite
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.12,1:18:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,opera La Boheme
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.12,1:18:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and the San Francisco Opera House
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.12,1:18:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,if you stand out during the intermission
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.12,1:18:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you're looking over San Francisco City Hall
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.12,1:18:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,a very very beautiful building
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.12,1:18:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was standing out there
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.12,1:19:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,during the break
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.28,1:19:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and a man came over
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.31,1:19:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and solicited me
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.31,1:19:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was 75
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.54,1:19:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.82,1:19:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but he did it in a way that
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.82,1:19:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always felt very
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.82,1:19:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,okay about that
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.82,1:19:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because I could tell the man was really lonely
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.82,1:19:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,he was really a lonely person
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.85,1:19:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and I felt compassion for his loneliness
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.91,1:19:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and I always felt like
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.91,1:19:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,saying if I could
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.91,1:19:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be with you in whatever way would please you
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.91,1:19:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,just out of your loneliness
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.91,1:19:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,it was his loneliness
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.91,1:19:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course they intuit
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.91,1:19:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you're safe or not safe
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.91,1:19:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,so he intuited that I was safe
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.91,1:19:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and I just said
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.91,1:19:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't really do it today
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.91,1:19:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,my wife is over there
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.91,1:19:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,oh
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.91,1:19:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,so I mean
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.91,1:19:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that kind of thing is perfectly okay
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.91,1:19:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing wrong with a person soliciting
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.91,1:20:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,he comes back to me and he goes
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.91,1:20:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm 75 years old
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.91,1:20:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're still hitting on you
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.77,1:20:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,well I felt sort of good about it
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.77,1:20:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,in a way too
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.77,1:20:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody gets hit on
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.41,1:20:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're 75
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.41,1:20:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,old and ugly
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.41,1:20:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,alright now we're going to take a break
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.41,1:20:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,for how long?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.41,1:20:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,it'll be about 15-20 minutes
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.41,1:20:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,alright thank you so much
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.41,1:20:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll see you after the break
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.41,1:20:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you're a great group
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.72,1:20:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the mic's set up
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.65,1:20:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm ready when you're ready
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.65,1:20:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,go
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.65,1:20:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,my question is actually somewhat technical
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.65,1:20:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and goes back to the workshop
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.65,1:20:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that you gave in LA in November
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.26,1:20:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,my question is about something
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.26,1:20:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that he mentioned in the LA workshop
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.26,1:21:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in November
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.26,1:21:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you talked about attention and intention
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.26,1:21:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm writing on that
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.26,1:21:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,as it relates to business and leadership
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.26,1:21:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and you gave some citations
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.26,1:21:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,for Medina
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.26,1:21:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but I couldn't find them
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.26,1:21:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and neither could my librarian
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.26,1:21:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I did write you
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.26,1:21:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it was spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.26,1:21:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean it was
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.26,1:21:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,psychiatric news
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.26,1:21:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Medina I have the
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.71,1:21:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,reference
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.06,1:21:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it's relatively recent
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.06,1:21:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I may have said
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.66,1:21:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,psychiatric news
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.66,1:21:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,there's two psychiatric newspapers
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.66,1:21:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I may have given you the wrong one
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.73,1:21:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Medina should be there
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.73,1:21:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,on the internet
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.73,1:21:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,he wrote several papers on the subject
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.05,1:21:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,if you send me another email
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.05,1:21:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get it for you
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.05,1:21:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I did answer the email
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.05,1:21:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember specifically answering the email
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.05,1:21:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and giving you the reference
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.05,1:22:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because I looked it back up again
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.05,1:22:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know I didn't receive it
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.05,1:22:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Medina yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.05,1:22:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,he wrote a series of three or four papers
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.21,1:22:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and they have to do with the power of intention
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.21,1:22:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,attention sets
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.21,1:22:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because it sets your priorities
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.21,1:22:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,which I thought is interesting
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.21,1:22:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it sets the screen from which you view the universe
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.21,1:22:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,would that be correct
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.37,1:22:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah it sets your prevailing overall intention
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.37,1:22:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.50,1:22:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.60,1:22:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it gave neuropsychiatric confirmation
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.67,1:22:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of what we've been teaching
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.67,1:22:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,about intention
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.67,1:22:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,neuropsychiatrically it's been confirmed
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.77,1:22:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so you might say
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.12,1:22:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in the highest court
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.15,1:22:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you're accountable
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.15,1:22:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,for what you did
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.15,1:22:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're morally responsible for your intention
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.15,1:22:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it can be a disparity
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.31,1:23:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,more than a question
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.68,1:23:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I have an experience
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.68,1:23:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to relate to you
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.22,1:23:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a memory of waking up
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.29,1:23:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,laying on my back
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.35,1:23:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was looking
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.35,1:23:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,up to the ceiling and the walls
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.35,1:23:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,had this paisley green wallpaper
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.35,1:23:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was a window on the south side of the house
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.35,1:23:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was a paper blind drawn down
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.35,1:23:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and light was streaming through this little crack
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.35,1:23:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was laying there just admiring
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.35,1:23:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,these dust particles
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.35,1:23:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was in the most profound bliss
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.35,1:23:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I was happier
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.42,1:23:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't express how the joy
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.42,1:23:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that I was experiencing
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.67,1:23:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a broken light fixture
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.67,1:23:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,on the ceiling
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.67,1:23:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and I could hear my mother
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.67,1:23:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and a woman that I knew in the other room
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.67,1:23:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,along with another woman that I didn't know
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.67,1:23:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and I could hear the tinkling of cups
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.31,1:23:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew they were drinking coffee or tea
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.08,1:23:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and the door opened
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.08,1:23:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and an eight year old girl stepped in the room
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.08,1:23:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,with long brown hair and a couple of teeth missing
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.08,1:24:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and smiled and turned back and told my mother
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.08,1:24:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,he's awake
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.11,1:24:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and then she walked over to the side of the bed
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.11,1:24:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and started playing with me
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.40,1:24:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was talking with her
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.40,1:24:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I was communicating with her and she couldn't hear me
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.53,1:24:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't roll over
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.53,1:24:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't do anything
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.53,1:24:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and I recognized in that moment
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.53,1:24:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that's right
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.53,1:24:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm stepping into my existence
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.53,1:24:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I was stepping into my existence
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.53,1:24:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,this was a period of my birth
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.53,1:24:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,just right after my birth
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.53,1:24:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't roll over
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.53,1:24:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't talk
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.59,1:24:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but I knew the people in the other room
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.75,1:24:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that this was my sister
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.75,1:24:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and it fled right after that
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.10,1:24:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,it was just gone
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.10,1:24:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,there was an opportunity for me
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.10,1:24:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing of a pre-existence
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.10,1:24:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing of a time before this life
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.10,1:24:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,there was another time
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.50,1:24:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was 19
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.50,1:24:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in a motorcycle accident
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.50,1:24:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was killed
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.50,1:25:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was gone for a period of time
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.10,1:25:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I had an opportunity to sit with three
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.10,1:25:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,what I thought were individuals
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.10,1:25:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and I thought that I was through
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.10,1:25:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,with this opportunity on earth
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.10,1:25:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,there were spirits, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.10,1:25:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,yes
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.22,1:25:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was ecstatic to be there
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.22,1:25:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I could feel again this most profound love
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.22,1:25:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time my definition of it was
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.22,1:25:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,there were tens of thousands of previous loved ones
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.22,1:25:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that had been on this earth
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.22,1:25:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,were surrounding me
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.22,1:25:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was just overwhelmed with the joy
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.22,1:25:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and the love of being there
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.22,1:25:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and they said slow down just a minute
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.22,1:25:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you want to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.22,1:25:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and I said what do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.22,1:25:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm through with the thing on earth
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.22,1:25:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm here, this is what I want to do
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.22,1:25:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and they said please hold on a moment
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.28,1:25:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and they left and they retreated
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.28,1:25:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,there were three originally
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.28,1:25:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and two returned and said listen
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.28,1:25:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,there's so much more to be accomplished
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.28,1:25:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and I tried to make deals
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.63,1:25:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with them to stay
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.63,1:25:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and they got a kick out of it
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.63,1:25:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,they thought that was pretty funny
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.63,1:26:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,they said it doesn't work like that
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.63,1:26:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,just come back
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.63,1:26:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and I recognized they were going to keep insisting
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.63,1:26:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that I come back until I make my own decision to be here
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.63,1:26:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and so I did
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.63,1:26:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and I wasn't very happy about it
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.02,1:26:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,for the longest time I felt
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.85,1:26:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,why did I have to come back?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.10,1:26:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,well you get a chance to leave again, don't worry
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.10,1:26:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I get that
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.45,1:26:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to share this with you
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.44,1:26:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you doctor
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.44,1:26:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,yes I like it
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.44,1:26:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,visitors from other dimensions
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.98,1:26:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,angelic visitors
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.17,1:26:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes they have to turn back
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.54,1:26:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes you can let them rest
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.54,1:26:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.18,1:26:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,my question is about karma
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.71,1:26:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.71,1:26:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,here in the United States
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.71,1:27:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I think most people
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.71,1:27:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,when you say the word karma
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.71,1:27:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,they mean the sum total
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.71,1:27:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of all the karmic merit
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.71,1:27:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we've accrued
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.71,1:27:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,during the course of our life
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.71,1:27:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,what we do
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.71,1:27:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but when I was reading about
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.71,1:27:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic theory
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.71,1:27:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw the mention of two other types of karma
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.71,1:27:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,one being
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.71,1:27:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the planet earth
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.71,1:27:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,has its own karma
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.71,1:27:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and sometimes we
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.71,1:27:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,have acts of nature
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.71,1:27:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that affect us
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.71,1:27:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and that seems
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.71,1:27:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty reasonable
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.71,1:27:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but the third type of karma
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.71,1:27:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that's been mentioned in my reading
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.71,1:27:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is group karma
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.71,1:27:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,where the activities
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.71,1:27:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,initiated by others can forcefully
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.71,1:27:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,impinge on your life
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.71,1:27:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,so that things can happen
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.74,1:27:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to you that really have nothing to do
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.74,1:27:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,with your individual karma
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.74,1:27:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,they're more about
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.74,1:27:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the karma of the people
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.74,1:27:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,doing it
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.74,1:28:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's really
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.74,1:28:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,just that you were there
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.74,1:28:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,at the wrong time and place
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.74,1:28:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and it happened to you
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.74,1:28:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so you agree
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.88,1:28:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.88,1:28:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,yes there's group karma
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.62,1:28:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,see just by agreement
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.65,1:28:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,with the culture you now have
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.65,1:28:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,for better or worse
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.87,1:28:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but it can be also for better
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.29,1:28:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,people forget that it can be for better
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.29,1:28:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,right group consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.29,1:28:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,can really affect
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.29,1:28:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,our lives
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.29,1:28:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.60,1:28:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you know you see massive
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.87,1:28:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,phenomena tsunamis
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.87,1:28:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,earthquakes and plagues
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.74,1:28:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that affect you know
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.74,1:28:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,large populations of people
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.26,1:28:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,hello
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.38,1:28:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,my question is about
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.38,1:29:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego and self sabotage
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.38,1:29:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,like suffering
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.38,1:29:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don't mean like
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.38,1:29:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you know a little guilt here
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.38,1:29:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,pride there
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.57,1:29:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean like misery
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.57,1:29:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,where you almost like choose that
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.63,1:29:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,where you rather be miserable
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.63,1:29:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.63,1:29:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,how to transcend that
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.63,1:29:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,what's the question?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.50,1:29:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,um
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.50,1:29:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,how to get out of like self sabotage
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.53,1:29:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of like a
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.53,1:29:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,oh self sabotage is a label
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.53,1:29:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,ok
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.14,1:29:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody has ups and downs
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.14,1:29:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you know along the pathway
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.14,1:29:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and every time you have a down
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.14,1:29:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't label it self sabotage
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.26,1:29:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you know that's sort of
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.06,1:29:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,pop psychology you know
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.86,1:29:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not really self sabotage
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.86,1:29:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,lots of painful feelings
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.88,1:29:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in this lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.88,1:29:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't call them all self sabotage
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.88,1:29:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't live long enough to die
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.88,1:29:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.88,1:30:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,lowered feelings
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.00,1:30:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,lowered feelings you know
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.00,1:30:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.17,1:30:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.17,1:30:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,they come up to be recognized
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.17,1:30:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and that if you can see the essence of them
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.23,1:30:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you forgive that within yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.23,1:30:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,which is associated with that
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.79,1:30:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.02,1:30:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,hi doc
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.02,1:30:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I really don't have a question
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.02,1:30:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to be in your presence for a moment
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.02,1:30:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,yes indeed
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.02,1:30:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you so much
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.02,1:30:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,love you doc
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.04,1:30:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,ok
Dialogue: 0,1:30:57.03,1:30:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that guy's ok huh
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.03,1:31:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,no
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.10,1:31:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the pathway of devotion you see
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.10,1:31:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that's why the hands folded this way
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.10,1:31:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,are so
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.10,1:31:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,appealing to me
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.10,1:31:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that's why I like being in Korea
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.10,1:31:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,amongst Indian people
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.17,1:31:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,where the devotion
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.81,1:31:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you know to give recognition
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.81,1:31:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to the divinity within the other
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.81,1:31:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is so charming
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.10,1:31:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a question either
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.99,1:31:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I just
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.22,1:31:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I have so much panic and fear
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.22,1:31:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,about getting up in front of people
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.22,1:31:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought I'd come up here
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.22,1:31:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and just experience it out every time I come
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.22,1:31:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're all going to laugh at your ridiculing
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.22,1:31:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and probably attack you at night
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.22,1:31:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,now we all
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.22,1:31:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,are on your side
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.22,1:31:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,for the courage to do that
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.31,1:31:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and face it
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.31,1:31:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,years ago I had stage fright
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.31,1:31:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't give a lecture to two student nurses
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.31,1:31:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember you saying that
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.24,1:31:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't hold eye contact
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.24,1:32:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,with someone for over 30 seconds
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.24,1:32:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,most of my life
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.24,1:32:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and then one day I discovered
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.24,1:32:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that humor broke the back of it
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.24,1:32:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so I want you to keep laughing
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.50,1:32:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and make everything
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.50,1:32:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,see the comedy in everything that exists
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.50,1:32:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,as I say I was frozen with terror
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.59,1:32:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.59,1:32:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,by accident said something funny
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.59,1:32:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole crowd laughed
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.59,1:32:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,instantly all the anxiety went away
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.59,1:32:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've never had it since
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.59,1:32:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be funnier
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.59,1:32:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,see how ridiculous and absurd
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.59,1:32:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and funny life is
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.59,1:32:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,funny funny ha ha
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.98,1:32:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,can I shake your hand?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.16,1:32:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,how's it going?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.61,1:32:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,yo
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.61,1:32:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,he's a gung ho kind of guy
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.96,1:33:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,if you guys don't mind
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.96,1:33:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to see if you guys wouldn't mind
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.96,1:33:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,asking how many people are on the planet
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.96,1:33:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,above 600
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.34,1:33:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,oh we didn't ask that
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.79,1:33:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,no I used to keep track of it
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.79,1:33:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,on the bullet board
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.79,1:33:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,over 600
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.50,1:33:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,we have permission to ask this question
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.50,1:33:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,there's more than
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.88,1:33:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,5 people over 600
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.88,1:33:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,on the planet right now
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.13,1:33:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,more than 4
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.80,1:33:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,more than 5
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.83,1:33:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,4 on the planet
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.83,1:33:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,there's less than there was
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.83,1:33:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe that's why
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.83,1:33:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,oh yeah that's one of the reasons it came down
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.83,1:33:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that was a good question
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.83,1:33:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,so how many did I say there was?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.83,1:33:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,4
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.83,1:33:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,oh 4 I don't listen to myself
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.24,1:33:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,see 4 over 600
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.24,1:33:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is enough to counterbalance a huge amount
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.24,1:33:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of the population
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.37,1:34:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah that's very interesting
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.04,1:34:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so there's a 600 spot
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.14,1:34:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,out there available
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.14,1:34:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,money wins over peace
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.99,1:34:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so we're selling it for $10,000
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.15,1:34:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.15,1:34:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you very much
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.15,1:34:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you guys
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.15,1:34:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,he's a great guy
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.15,1:34:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we've met him under other circumstances
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.15,1:34:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,no question again doc
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.05,1:34:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to come and thank you
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.05,1:34:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,ah yes thank you very much
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.05,1:34:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you very much
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.05,1:34:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,can I get a picture?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.33,1:34:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,yes
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.78,1:34:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,my pleasure
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.61,1:34:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I take such good pictures
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.61,1:35:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,hello
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.29,1:35:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a question about
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.29,1:35:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,creativity
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.29,1:35:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a musician and a singer
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.29,1:35:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and my intention is that my
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.29,1:35:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,music would
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.29,1:35:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,serve
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.29,1:35:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,be of the greatest service and good
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.29,1:35:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm wondering
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.09,1:35:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,how do I do that
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.09,1:35:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the greatest beauty that you can
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.09,1:35:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,summon up
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.25,1:35:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the greatest love or sympathy
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.25,1:35:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean whatever it is you're trying to bring forth in your music
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.25,1:35:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,beauty itself
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.50,1:35:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is uplifting
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.50,1:35:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is it because even more of those things
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.50,1:35:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is it possible to
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.01,1:35:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,create a song that
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.01,1:35:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates higher than I do
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.01,1:35:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,no
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.98,1:35:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the answer is correct
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.98,1:35:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.66,1:35:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,does the
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.81,1:35:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say a song
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.90,1:35:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 400
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.90,1:36:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,could I give
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.90,1:36:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,a performance that's higher
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.90,1:36:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,than 400 or a performance that's lower
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.90,1:36:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,or will the performance of that song
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.90,1:36:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't say that
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.90,1:36:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because right in the middle
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.90,1:36:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say of a song at 400
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.90,1:36:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and you at 400
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.90,1:36:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll suddenly feel a surge of incredible
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.42,1:36:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,inspiration and love
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.42,1:36:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly you shoot all the way up
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.42,1:36:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I see
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.58,1:36:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean this audience
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.58,1:36:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,blows me out all the time
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.58,1:36:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because once you feel that energy
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.02,1:36:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,come up from the crowd
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.02,1:36:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it summons forth
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.02,1:36:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it's reciprocal in yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.02,1:36:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,so you're getting a reflection back
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.02,1:36:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which you're saying
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.02,1:36:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you're sending out
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.02,1:36:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,so the more love you send out to your audience
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.02,1:36:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the more they'll
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.02,1:36:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,reflect back to you
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.02,1:36:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to have a loving audience
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.02,1:36:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is to just be crazy in love with the audience
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.02,1:36:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I see
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.88,1:36:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the Stones used to do that
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.88,1:36:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean he just gets high on
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.88,1:37:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the crowd doesn't he
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.88,1:37:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry who?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.10,1:37:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The Stones
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.10,1:37:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The Stones yes
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.10,1:37:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,um
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.10,1:37:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,as an
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.33,1:37:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,expression of gratitude may I offer
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.33,1:37:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,a very short
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.33,1:37:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,a very short piece of a song that I
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.33,1:37:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,composed very short
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.33,1:37:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,a tidbit of a song
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.33,1:37:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,a tidbit of a song
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.33,1:37:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,for all that
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.97,1:37:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you are
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.13,1:37:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and all you are not
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.13,1:37:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I am
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.13,1:37:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,so thankful
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.13,1:37:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,for all that
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.22,1:37:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we've got
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.32,1:37:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you are the reason
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.32,1:37:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,my purpose
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.32,1:37:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,for breathing
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.32,1:37:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.32,1:37:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,for sharing
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.32,1:37:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,this beautiful
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.54,1:37:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.15,1:38:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and I love
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.18,1:38:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,let's hear it for that guy
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.30,1:38:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,next generation
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.30,1:38:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,hi
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.66,1:38:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that was beautiful
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.94,1:38:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that was very nice
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.94,1:38:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I closed my eyes
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.98,1:38:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I also just came up to
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.98,1:38:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,sit with you
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.98,1:38:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and a question kind of came through
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.98,1:38:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is about
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.98,1:38:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,what is it that
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.98,1:38:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is seeking enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.07,1:38:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,very good question nobody
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.26,1:38:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.26,1:38:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just like the no mind thing then
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.26,1:38:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the no mind question
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.26,1:39:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so there's no mind nobody's seeking it
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.26,1:39:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the seekingness is happening of its own
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.26,1:39:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's nobody that is seeking
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.26,1:39:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,seeking this
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.26,1:39:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,like it returns to its source
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.26,1:39:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness wishes
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.77,1:39:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.77,1:39:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it returns to its source
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.22,1:39:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're the witness participant
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.22,1:39:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,observer of that
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.63,1:39:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say it drags you along
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.66,1:39:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,by your agreement
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.66,1:39:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,by your agreement
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.95,1:39:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's forced against their will
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.95,1:39:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,into an enlightened state
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.78,1:39:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,so you let go resisting the nature
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.78,1:39:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the nature
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.78,1:39:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.78,1:39:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,which is to return to its source
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.78,1:39:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,okay so
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.93,1:39:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no ego involved
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.93,1:39:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,not really
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.93,1:39:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,can you say it's consciousness seeking its source
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.93,1:39:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness is the field
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.93,1:39:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,in which all this phenomena is happening
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.93,1:39:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're the witness observer
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.93,1:39:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,there it is
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.93,1:39:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you're the witness observer
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.93,1:40:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,yes when I'm sitting here
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.93,1:40:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,with you and you're telling it to me
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.93,1:40:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,somehow something is transmitted
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.93,1:40:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,through no mind
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.93,1:40:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what it is but it's like a transmission
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.93,1:40:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that happens
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.93,1:40:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and it seems to happen whenever
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.93,1:40:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you look into my eyes
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.93,1:40:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.96,1:40:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I think everybody's going to come and look into you
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.96,1:40:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,makes sense
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.96,1:40:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah makes sense
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.11,1:40:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's what happens
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.11,1:40:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to reflect back to you
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.11,1:40:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the reality of that which you are
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.11,1:40:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that's all I do
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.75,1:40:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,all you're doing is witnessing yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.68,1:40:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so I shine back to you
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.68,1:40:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the radiance of the self which is you
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.70,1:40:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's the
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.70,1:40:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,godhead source
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.70,1:40:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the source that is being reflected
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.70,1:40:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the essence of that which you are
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.47,1:40:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is reflected back
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.47,1:40:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,through my recognition of it in you
Dialogue: 0,1:40:54.47,1:40:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,right
Dialogue: 0,1:40:57.02,1:40:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like when I put words to it
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.02,1:41:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it's gone
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.02,1:41:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,yes that's exactly it
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.02,1:41:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,just look at the tree and fall over
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.02,1:41:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,weeping with joy
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.02,1:41:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,don't call it a tree
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.02,1:41:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,don't call it weeping with joy
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.02,1:41:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,just fall on the ground
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.02,1:41:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you Susan
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.02,1:41:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,let the worms have you
Dialogue: 0,1:41:18.46,1:41:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,if they want
Dialogue: 0,1:41:21.74,1:41:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,well worms got to eat too
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.41,1:41:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.50,1:41:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree with her
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.50,1:41:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to ask you a question
Dialogue: 0,1:41:30.50,1:41:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I get lost in your eyes
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.50,1:41:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and I have to get the video
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.50,1:41:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to know what you said to me
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.08,1:41:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to express our gratitude
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.08,1:41:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,for your teachings
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.08,1:41:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to express our gratitude
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.08,1:41:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for your teachings
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.27,1:41:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and English doesn't do it
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.39,1:41:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope perhaps this expresses
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.39,1:41:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,what it feels like
Dialogue: 0,1:41:52.97,1:41:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,when I'm in this presence
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.97,1:41:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,oh how beautiful
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.93,1:41:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you very much
Dialogue: 0,1:41:59.93,1:42:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.70,1:42:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how to explain it
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.70,1:42:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it's
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.70,1:42:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like a radiance
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.21,1:42:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,a radiance
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.21,1:42:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the radiance you see the beauty of the tree
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.21,1:42:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,outlined against the light in the back
Dialogue: 0,1:42:15.21,1:42:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you so much
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.21,1:42:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it's almost like a rainbow
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.21,1:42:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,beautiful thank you
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.23,1:42:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,well I want to thank both of you
Dialogue: 0,1:42:30.06,1:42:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for the opportunity to be here
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.28,1:42:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.24,1:42:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,if I can even articulate this question
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.24,1:42:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you'll allow me to use
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.24,1:42:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the David Hawkins experience from birth on
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.24,1:42:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to try to articulate it
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.24,1:42:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,as a reference
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.24,1:42:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe I've understood you to say
Dialogue: 0,1:42:47.24,1:42:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that at about 3 you realized you came in
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.24,1:42:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,at maybe 8.50
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.24,1:42:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,no I didn't realize that at 8.30
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.56,1:42:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,now looking back on it maybe you realized that
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.56,1:42:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,at 8.30
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.56,1:42:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I came out of nothingness
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.56,1:43:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,into existence
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.10,1:43:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was not pleased
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.10,1:43:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to discover that I existed
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.71,1:43:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,as soon as I realized that I existed
Dialogue: 0,1:43:08.71,1:43:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,immediately up came the fear of non-existence
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.71,1:43:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.37,1:43:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe one time you expressed that as
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.37,1:43:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you came in from the void
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.37,1:43:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,yes
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.37,1:43:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason I'm asking that question
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.37,1:43:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is because you had
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.37,1:43:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,as you matured in this physical body
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.37,1:43:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,there were other experiences in the snowbank
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.37,1:43:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,there were experiences of the state of being in hell
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.37,1:43:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,there was experiencing the condition
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.37,1:43:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe you expressed on time
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.37,1:43:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience of conditioning enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,1:43:37.37,1:43:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,which would be a 600 or 700
Dialogue: 0,1:43:39.37,1:43:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and then later experiencing the void again
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.37,1:43:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is there something about our physiological maturation
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.37,1:43:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that would prevent
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.37,1:43:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,us from realizing those states
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.37,1:43:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you came in at 8.50
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.37,1:43:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and later on you re-experienced 8.50
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.37,1:43:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,with other things in between
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.50,1:43:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really understand the question
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.50,1:43:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it says
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.50,1:43:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual evolution is not a
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.50,1:44:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,linear
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.50,1:44:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,linear like this
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.50,1:44:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens is you
Dialogue: 0,1:44:05.50,1:44:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,surpass a certain energy field
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.50,1:44:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and flash you got the whole thing
Dialogue: 0,1:44:09.50,1:44:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that opens up the pathway
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.50,1:44:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to the next realization
Dialogue: 0,1:44:13.50,1:44:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which could be 10 years later
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.04,1:44:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in a linear sequence
Dialogue: 0,1:44:18.04,1:44:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it was funny to me
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.04,1:44:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and it probably is the question of linearity
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.04,1:44:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,why someone could come in at 8.50
Dialogue: 0,1:44:24.04,1:44:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and go through the experience
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.04,1:44:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of moving through the 600, 700
Dialogue: 0,1:44:28.04,1:44:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that kind of thing
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.52,1:44:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you're trying to give it some chronological sequence
Dialogue: 0,1:44:32.52,1:44:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that doesn't work that way
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.52,1:44:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it could have happened in the other direction
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.52,1:44:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,ah, thank you very much
